148static const Int ATTACK_PRIORITY_DEFAULT = 1;
149//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
151//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
152AttackPriorityInfo::AttackPriorityInfo() :m_defaultPriority(ATTACK_PRIORITY_DEFAULT), m_priorityMap(NULL)
153{
154 m_name.clear();
155}
156
157//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
159//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
160AttackPriorityInfo::~AttackPriorityInfo()
161{
162 if (m_priorityMap) delete m_priorityMap;
163 m_priorityMap = NULL;
164}
165
166//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
168//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
169void AttackPriorityInfo::setPriority(const ThingTemplate *tThing, Int priority)
170{
171 if (tThing==NULL) return;
172 if (m_priorityMap==NULL) {
173 m_priorityMap = NEW AttackPriorityMap; // STL type, so impractical to use memorypool
174 }
175 tThing = (const ThingTemplate *)tThing->getFinalOverride();
176 Int &thePriority = (*m_priorityMap)[tThing];
177 thePriority = priority;
178}
179
181//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
182Int AttackPriorityInfo::getPriority(const ThingTemplate *tThing) const
183{
184 Int priority = m_defaultPriority;
185 if (tThing==NULL) return priority;
186 tThing = (const ThingTemplate *)tThing->getFinalOverride();
187 if (m_priorityMap && !m_priorityMap->empty()) {
188 AttackPriorityMap::const_iterator it = m_priorityMap->find(tThing);
189 if (it != m_priorityMap->end())
190 {
191 priority = (*it).second;
192 }
193 }
194 return priority;
195}
196
197#ifdef _DEBUG
199//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
200void AttackPriorityInfo::dumpPriorityInfo(void)
201{
202#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
203 DEBUG_LOG(("Attack priority '%s', default %d\n", m_name.str(), m_defaultPriority));
204 if (m_priorityMap==NULL) return;
205 for (AttackPriorityMap::const_iterator it = m_priorityMap->begin(); it != m_priorityMap->end(); ++it)
206 {
207 const ThingTemplate *tThing = (*it).first;
208 Int priority = (*it).second;
209 DEBUG_LOG((" Thing '%s' priority %d\n",tThing->getName().str(), priority));
210 }
211#endif
212}
213#endif
214
215// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
217// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
218void AttackPriorityInfo::reset( void )
219{
220
221 // clear name just to be clean
222 m_name.clear();
223
224 // go back to default priority
225 m_defaultPriority = ATTACK_PRIORITY_DEFAULT;
226
227 // delete the priority map if present
228 if( m_priorityMap )
229 {
230
231 delete m_priorityMap;
232 m_priorityMap = NULL;
233
234 } // end if
235
236} // end reset
237
238// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
240// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
241void AttackPriorityInfo::crc( Xfer *xfer )
242{
243
244} // end crc
245
246// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
250// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
251void AttackPriorityInfo::xfer( Xfer *xfer )
252{
253
254 // version
255 XferVersion currentVersion = 1;
256 XferVersion version = currentVersion;
257 xfer->xferVersion( &version, currentVersion );
258
259 // name
260 xfer->xferAsciiString( &m_name );
261
262 xfer->xferInt( &m_defaultPriority );
263
264 //
265 // priority map count, note there is question to the following code that is
266 // commented out in that we're not sure it returns the correct number of elements
267 // in the map. To be safe, we're getting the count by manually counting the
268 // elements ourselves as we iterate through them
269 //
270 // Please KEEP the below code here for reference
271 // UnsignedShort priorityMapCount = m_priorityMap ? m_priorityMap->size() : 0;
272 //
273 UnsignedShort priorityMapCount = 0;
274 if( m_priorityMap )
275 {
276 AttackPriorityMap::const_iterator it;
277
278 for( it = m_priorityMap->begin(); it != m_priorityMap->end(); ++it )
279 ++priorityMapCount;
280
281 } // end if
282 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &priorityMapCount );
283
284 // priority map
285 AsciiString thingTemplateName;
286 const ThingTemplate *thingTemplate;
287 Int priority;
288 if( xfer->getXferMode() == XFER_SAVE )
289 {
290
291 if( m_priorityMap )
292 {
293
294 // iterate all the entries
295 AttackPriorityMap::const_iterator it;
296 UnsignedShort count = 0;
297 for( it = m_priorityMap->begin(); it != m_priorityMap->end(); ++it )
298 {
299
300 // keep a count for sanity
301 ++count;
302
303 // write thing template name
304 thingTemplate = (*it).first;
305 thingTemplateName = thingTemplate->getName();
306 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH( thingTemplateName.isEmpty() == FALSE,
307 ("AttackPriorityInfo::xfer - Writing an empty thing template name\n") );
308 xfer->xferAsciiString( &thingTemplateName );
309
310 // write priority
311 priority = (*it).second;
312 xfer->xferInt( &priority );
313
314 } // end for i
315
316 // sanity
317 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH( count == priorityMapCount,
318 ("AttackPriorityInfo::xfer - Mismatch in priority map size. Size() method returned '%d' but actual iteration count was '%d'\n",
319 priorityMapCount, count) );
320
321 } // end if
322
323 } // end if, save
324 else
325 {
326
327 // read all entries
328 for( UnsignedShort i = 0; i < priorityMapCount; ++i )
329 {
330
331 // read thing template name, and get template
332 xfer->xferAsciiString( &thingTemplateName );
333 thingTemplate = TheThingFactory->findTemplate( thingTemplateName );
334 if( thingTemplate == NULL )
335 {
336
337 DEBUG_CRASH(( "AttackPriorityInfo::xfer - Unable to find thing template '%s'\n",
338 thingTemplateName.str() ));
339 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
340
341 } // end if
342
343 // read priority
344 xfer->xferInt( &priority );
345
346 // set priority (this will allocate the map on the first call as well)
347 setPriority( thingTemplate, priority );
348
349 } // end for
350
351 } // end else, load
352
353} // end xfer

361} // end loadPostProcess

363// ScriptEngine class
364static const FieldParse TheTemplateFieldParseTable[] =
365{
366 { "InternalName", INI::parseAsciiString,NULL, offsetof( Template, m_internalName ) },
367 { "UIName", INI::parseAsciiString,NULL, offsetof( Template, m_uiName ) },
368 { "UIName2", INI::parseAsciiString,NULL, offsetof( Template, m_uiName2 ) },
369 { "HelpText", INI::parseAsciiString,NULL, offsetof( Template, m_helpText ) },
370 { NULL, NULL, NULL, 0 } // keep this last
371};
372
373//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
377//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
378void ScriptEngine::parseScriptAction( INI* ini )
379{
380 // parse the ini weapon definition
381 ActionTemplate scriptTemplate;
382 ini->initFromINI( &scriptTemplate, TheTemplateFieldParseTable );
383 if (TheScriptEngine) {
384 TheScriptEngine->addActionTemplateInfo(&scriptTemplate);
385 }
386}
387
388//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
393//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
394void ScriptEngine::addActionTemplateInfo( Template *actionTemplate)
395{
396 Int i;
397 for (i=0; i<ScriptAction::NUM_ITEMS; i++) {
398 if (m_actionTemplates[i].m_internalName == actionTemplate->m_internalName) {
399 m_actionTemplates[i].m_uiName = actionTemplate->m_uiName;
400 m_actionTemplates[i].m_uiName2 = actionTemplate->m_uiName2;
401 m_actionTemplates[i].m_helpText = actionTemplate->m_helpText;
402 return;
403 }
404 }
405 DEBUG_LOG(("Couldn't find script action named %s\n", actionTemplate->m_internalName.str()));
406}
407
408//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
412//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
413void ScriptEngine::parseScriptCondition( INI* ini )
414{
415 // parse the ini weapon definition
416 ActionTemplate scriptTemplate;
417 ini->initFromINI( &scriptTemplate, TheTemplateFieldParseTable );
418 if (TheScriptEngine) {
419 TheScriptEngine->addConditionTemplateInfo(&scriptTemplate);
420 }
421}
422
423//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
428//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
429void ScriptEngine::addConditionTemplateInfo( Template *actionTemplate)
430{
431 Int i;
432 for (i=0; i<Condition::NUM_ITEMS; i++) {
433 if (m_conditionTemplates[i].m_internalName == actionTemplate->m_internalName) {
434 m_conditionTemplates[i].m_uiName = actionTemplate->m_uiName;
435 m_conditionTemplates[i].m_uiName2 = actionTemplate->m_uiName2;
436 m_conditionTemplates[i].m_helpText = actionTemplate->m_helpText;
437 return;
438 }
439 }
440 DEBUG_LOG(("Couldn't find script condition named %s", actionTemplate->m_internalName.str()));
441}

484//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
485//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
486ScriptEngine::~ScriptEngine()
487{
488 if (st_DebugDLL) {
489 FARPROC proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "DestroyDebugDialog");
490 if (proc) {
491 proc();
492 }
493
494 FreeLibrary(st_DebugDLL);
495 st_DebugDLL = NULL;
496 }
497
498 if (st_ParticleDLL) {
499 FARPROC proc = GetProcAddress(st_ParticleDLL, "DestroyParticleSystemDialog");
500 if (proc) {
501 proc();
502 }
503
504 FreeLibrary(st_ParticleDLL);
505 st_ParticleDLL = NULL;
506 }
507
508#ifdef DO_VTUNE_STUFF
509 _cleanUpVTune();
510#endif
511
512 reset(); // just in case.
513#ifdef COUNT_SCRIPT_USAGE
514 Int i;
515 for (i=0; i<ScriptAction::NUM_ITEMS; i++) {
516 DEBUG_LOG(("ScriptAction%d, %4d, %s, %s, %s\n", i, m_actionTemplates[i].m_numTimesUsed,
517 m_actionTemplates[i].m_internalName.str(), m_actionTemplates[i].m_firstMapUsed.str(),
518 m_actionTemplates[i].m_uiName.str()));
519 }
520 for (i=0; i<Condition::NUM_ITEMS; i++) {
521 DEBUG_LOG(("ScriptCondition%d, %4d, %s, %s, %s\n", i, m_conditionTemplates[i].m_numTimesUsed,
522 m_conditionTemplates[i].m_internalName.str(), m_conditionTemplates[i].m_firstMapUsed.str(),
523 m_conditionTemplates[i].m_uiName.str()));
524 }
525#endif
526
527} // end ~ScriptEngine

531//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
532void ScriptEngine::init( void )
533{
534 if (TheGlobalData->m_windowed)
535 if (TheGlobalData->m_scriptDebug) {
536 st_DebugDLL = LoadLibrary("DebugWindow.dll");
537 } else {
538 st_DebugDLL = NULL;
539 }
540
541 if (TheGlobalData->m_particleEdit) {
542 st_ParticleDLL = LoadLibrary("ParticleEditor.dll");
543 } else {
544 st_ParticleDLL = NULL;
545 }
546
547 if (st_DebugDLL) {
548 FARPROC proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "CreateDebugDialog");
549 if (proc) {
550 proc();
551 }
552 }
553
554 if (st_ParticleDLL) {
555 FARPROC proc = GetProcAddress(st_ParticleDLL, "CreateParticleSystemDialog");
556 if (proc) {
557 proc();
558 }
559 }
560
561#ifdef DO_VTUNE_STUFF
562 _initVTune();
563#endif
564
565#ifdef SPECIAL_SCRIPT_PROFILING
566#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
567 m_numFrames=0;
568 m_totalUpdateTime=0;
569 m_maxUpdateTime=0;
570#endif
571#endif
572
573 if (TheScriptActions) {
574 TheScriptActions->init();
575 }
576 if (TheScriptConditions) {
577 TheScriptConditions->init();
578 }
579 /* Recipe for adding an action:
580 1. In Scripts.h, add an enum element to enum ScriptActionType just before NUM_ITEMS.
581 2. Go to the end of this section of templates, and create a template.
582 3. Go to ScriptActions.h and add a protected method.
583 4. Go to ScriptActions.cpp, and add your enum to the
584 switch in ScriptActions::executeAction to call your method in 3 above.
585 */
586

4109 /* Recipe for adding a condition:
4110 1. In Scripts.h, add an enum element to enum ConditionType just before NUM_ITEMS.
4111 2. Go to the end of this section of templates, and create a template.
4112 3. Go to ScriptConditions.h and add a protected method.
4113 4. Go to ScriptConditions.cpp, and add your enum to the
4114 switch in ScriptConditions::evaluateCondition to call your method in 3 above.
4115 */
4116
4117 // Set up condition templates.
4118 curTemplate = &m_conditionTemplates[Condition::CONDITION_FALSE];
4119 curTemplate->m_internalName = "CONDITION_FALSE";

4123 curTemplate->m_uiStrings[0] = "False.";

4131 curTemplate->m_parameters[2] = Parameter::INT;
4132 curTemplate->m_numUiStrings = 3;
4133 curTemplate->m_uiStrings[0] = "Counter ";
4134 curTemplate->m_uiStrings[1] = " IS ";
4135 curTemplate->m_uiStrings[2] = " ";
4136
4137 curTemplate = &m_conditionTemplates[Condition::UNIT_HEALTH];

5273//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5275//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5276void ScriptEngine::reset( void )
5277{
5278 // setting FPS limit in case a script had changed it
5279 if (TheGameEngine && TheGlobalData)
5280 TheGameEngine->setFramesPerSecondLimit(TheGlobalData->m_framesPerSecondLimit);
5281
5282 if (TheScriptActions) {
5283 TheScriptActions->reset();
5284 }
5285 if (TheScriptConditions) {
5286 TheScriptConditions->reset();
5287 }
5288 m_numCounters = 1;
5289 m_numAttackInfo = 1;
5290 m_numFlags = 1;
5291 m_endGameTimer = -1;
5292 m_closeWindowTimer = -1;
5293
5294 m_callingTeam = NULL;
5295 m_callingObject = NULL;
5296 m_conditionTeam = NULL;
5297 m_conditionObject = NULL;
5298 m_currentPlayer = NULL;
5299 m_skirmishHumanPlayer = NULL;
5300 m_frameObjectCountChanged = 0;
5301
5302 m_shownMPLocalDefeatWindow = FALSE;
5303
5304 Int i;
5305 for (i=0; i<MAX_COUNTERS; i++) {
5306 m_counters[i].value = 0;
5307 m_counters[i].isCountdownTimer = false;
5308 m_counters[i].name.clear();
5309 }
5310 for (i=0; i<MAX_FLAGS; i++) {
5311 m_flags[i].value = false;
5312 m_flags[i].name.clear();
5313 }
5314
5315 m_breezeInfo.m_direction = PI/3;
5316 m_breezeInfo.m_directionVec.x = Sin(m_breezeInfo.m_direction);
5317 m_breezeInfo.m_directionVec.y = Cos(m_breezeInfo.m_direction);
5318 m_breezeInfo.m_intensity = 0.07f*PI/4;
5319 m_breezeInfo.m_lean = 0.07f*PI/4;
5320 m_breezeInfo.m_breezePeriod = LOGICFRAMES_PER_SECOND * 5;
5321 m_breezeInfo.m_randomness = 0.2f;
5322 m_breezeInfo.m_breezeVersion = 0;
5323
5324 m_freezeByScript = FALSE;
5325 m_objectsShouldReceiveDifficultyBonus = TRUE;
5326 m_ChooseVictimAlwaysUsesNormal = false;
5327
5328#ifdef SPECIAL_SCRIPT_PROFILING
5329#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
5330 if (m_numFrames > 1) {
5331 DEBUG_LOG(("\n***SCRIPT ENGINE STATS %.0f frames:\n", m_numFrames));
5332 DEBUG_LOG(("Avg time to update %.3f milisec\n", 1000*m_totalUpdateTime/m_numFrames));
5333 DEBUG_LOG((" Max time to update %.3f miliseconds.\n", m_maxUpdateTime*1000));
5334 }
5335 m_numFrames=0;
5336 m_totalUpdateTime=0;
5337 m_maxUpdateTime=0;
5338
5339 Int numToDump;
5340 if (TheSidesList) {
5341 for (numToDump=0; numToDump<10; numToDump++) {
5342 Real maxTime = 0;
5343 Script *maxScript = NULL;
5344 /* Run through scripts & set condition team names. */
5345 for (i=0; i<TheSidesList->getNumSides(); i++) {
5346 ScriptList *pSL = TheSidesList->getSideInfo(i)->getScriptList();
5347 if (!pSL) continue;
5348 if (pSL == NULL) continue;
5349 Script *pScr;
5350 for (pScr = pSL->getScript(); pScr; pScr=pScr->getNext()) {
5351 if (pScr->getConditionTime()>maxTime) {
5352 maxTime = pScr->getConditionTime();
5353 maxScript = pScr;
5354 }
5355 }
5356 ScriptGroup *pGroup;
5357 for (pGroup = pSL->getScriptGroup(); pGroup; pGroup=pGroup->getNext()) {
5358 for (pScr = pGroup->getScript(); pScr; pScr=pScr->getNext()) {
5359 if (pScr->getConditionTime()>maxTime) {
5360 maxTime = pScr->getConditionTime();
5361 maxScript = pScr;
5362 }
5363 }
5364 }
5365 }
5366 if (maxScript) {
5367 DEBUG_LOG((" SCRIPT %s total time %f seconds,\n evaluated %d times, avg execution %2.3f msec (Goal less than 0.05)\n",
5368 maxScript->getName().str(),
5369 maxScript->getConditionTime(), maxScript->getConditionCount(), 1000*maxScript->getConditionTime()/maxScript->getConditionCount()) );
5370 maxScript->addToConditionTime(-2*maxTime); // reset to negative.
5371 }
5372
5373 }
5374 DEBUG_LOG(("***\n"));
5375 }
5376#endif
5377#endif
5378
5379 _updateCurrentParticleCap();
5380
5381 VecSequentialScriptPtrIt seqScriptIt;
5382 for (seqScriptIt = m_sequentialScripts.begin(); seqScriptIt != m_sequentialScripts.end(); ) {
5383 cleanupSequentialScript(seqScriptIt, TRUE);
5384 }
5385
5386 // clear out all the lists of object types that were in the old map.
5387 for (AllObjectTypesIt it = m_allObjectTypeLists.begin(); it != m_allObjectTypeLists.end(); it = m_allObjectTypeLists.begin() ) {
5388 if (*it) {
5389 removeObjectTypes(*it);
5390 } else {
5391 m_allObjectTypeLists.erase(it);
5392 }
5393 }
5394 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH( m_allObjectTypeLists.empty() == TRUE, ("ScriptEngine::reset - m_allObjectTypeLists should be empty but is not!\n") );
5395
5396 // reset all the reveals that have taken place.
5397 m_namedReveals.clear();
5398
5399 // Clear the named objects list.
5400 m_namedObjects.clear();
5401
5402 m_completedVideo.clear();
5403 m_testingSpeech.clear();
5404 m_testingAudio.clear();
5405 m_uiInteractions.clear();
5406 for (i=0; i<MAX_PLAYER_COUNT; ++i)
5407 {
5408 m_triggeredSpecialPowers[i].clear();
5409 m_midwaySpecialPowers[i].clear();
5410 m_finishedSpecialPowers[i].clear();
5411 m_acquiredSciences[i].clear();
5412 m_completedUpgrades[i].clear();
5413 }
5414
5415 ScriptList::reset(); // Deletes scripts loaded when the map was loaded.
5416
5417 // reset the attack priority data
5418 for( i = 0; i < MAX_ATTACK_PRIORITIES; ++i )
5419 m_attackPriorityInfo[ i ].reset();
5420
5421 // clear out all of our object counts.
5422 for( i = 0; i < MAX_PLAYER_COUNT; ++i )
5423 m_objectCounts[i].clear();
5424
5425 // clear topple directions
5426 m_toppleDirections.clear();
5427
5428} // end reset
5429
5430//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5432//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5433void ScriptEngine::newMap( void )
5434{
5435 m_numCounters = 1;
5436 Int i;
5437 for (i=0; i<MAX_COUNTERS; i++) {
5438 m_counters[i].value = 0;
5439 m_counters[i].isCountdownTimer = false;
5440 m_counters[i].name.clear();
5441 }
5442 m_numFlags = 1;
5443 for (i=0; i<MAX_FLAGS; i++) {
5444 m_flags[i].value = false;
5445 m_flags[i].name.clear();
5446 }
5447 m_endGameTimer = -1;
5448 m_closeWindowTimer = -1;
5449#ifdef SPECIAL_SCRIPT_PROFILING
5450#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
5451 m_numFrames=0;
5452 m_totalUpdateTime=0;
5453 m_maxUpdateTime=0;
5454#endif
5455#endif
5456
5457 m_completedVideo.clear();
5458 m_testingSpeech.clear();
5459 m_testingAudio.clear();
5460 m_uiInteractions.clear();
5461 for (i=0; i<MAX_PLAYER_COUNT; ++i)
5462 {
5463 m_triggeredSpecialPowers[i].clear();
5464 m_midwaySpecialPowers[i].clear();
5465 m_finishedSpecialPowers[i].clear();
5466 m_acquiredSciences[i].clear();
5467 m_completedUpgrades[i].clear();
5468 }
5469
5470 /* Run through scripts & set condition team names. */
5471 for (i=0; i<TheSidesList->getNumSides(); i++) {
5472 ScriptList *pSL = TheSidesList->getSideInfo(i)->getScriptList();
5473 if (!pSL) continue;
5474 if (pSL == NULL) continue;
5475 Script *pScr;
5476 for (pScr = pSL->getScript(); pScr; pScr=pScr->getNext()) {
5477 checkConditionsForTeamNames(pScr);
5478 }
5479 ScriptGroup *pGroup;
5480 for (pGroup = pSL->getScriptGroup(); pGroup; pGroup=pGroup->getNext()) {
5481 for (pScr = pGroup->getScript(); pScr; pScr=pScr->getNext()) {
5482 checkConditionsForTeamNames(pScr);
5483 }
5484 }
5485 }
5486 m_firstUpdate = true;
5487
5488 m_fade = FADE_MULTIPLY; //default to a fade in from black.
5489 m_curFadeFrame = 0;
5490 m_minFade = 1.0f;
5491 m_maxFade = 0.0f;
5492 m_fadeFramesIncrease = 0;
5493 m_fadeFramesHold = 0;
5494 m_fadeFramesDecrease = FRAMES_TO_FADE_IN_AT_START;
5495 m_curFadeValue = 0.0f;
5496
5497} // end newMap
5498
5499//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5501//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5502DECLARE_PERF_TIMER(ScriptEngine)
5503void ScriptEngine::update( void )
5504{
5505 USE_PERF_TIMER(ScriptEngine)
5506#ifdef SPECIAL_SCRIPT_PROFILING
5507#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
5508 __int64 startTime64;
5509 double timeToUpdate=0.0f;
5510 __int64 endTime64,freq64;
5511 QueryPerformanceFrequency((LARGE_INTEGER *)&freq64);//LORENZEN'S NOTE_TO_SELF: USE THIS
5512 QueryPerformanceCounter((LARGE_INTEGER *)&startTime64);//LORENZEN'S NOTE_TO_SELF: USE THIS
5513/* dump out the named objects table. For extremely intense debug only. jba. :P
5514 for (VecNamedRequestsIt it = m_namedObjects.begin(); it != m_namedObjects.end(); ++it) {
5515 AsciiString name = it->first;
5516 Object * obj = it->second;
5517 if (obj && obj->getAIUpdateInterface())
5518 DEBUG_LOG(("%s=%x('%s'), isDead%d\n", name.str(), obj, obj->getName().str(), obj->getAIUpdateInterface()->isDead()));
5519 }
5520 DEBUG_LOG(("\n\n"));
5521*/
5522#endif
5523#endif
5524 if (m_firstUpdate) {
5525 createNamedCache();
5526 particleEditorUpdate();
5527 m_firstUpdate = false;
5528 } else {
5529 particleEditorUpdate();
5530 }
5531
5532 if (m_closeWindowTimer>0) {
5533 m_closeWindowTimer--;
5534 if (m_closeWindowTimer < 1) {
5535 TheScriptActions->closeWindows(FALSE); // Close victory or defeat windows.
5536 }
5537 }
5538 if (m_endGameTimer>0) {
5539 m_endGameTimer--;
5540 if (m_endGameTimer < 1) {
5541 // clear out all the game data
5542 /*GameMessage *msg =*/ TheMessageStream->appendMessage( GameMessage::MSG_CLEAR_GAME_DATA );
5543 //TheScriptActions->closeWindows(FALSE); // Close victory or defeat windows.
5544 }
5545 }
5546 _updateFrameNumber();
5547 if (isTimeFrozenDebug()) {
5548 st_LastCurrentFrame = st_CurrentFrame - 1; // Force us to get clean result from CanAppContinue
5549 return;
5550 }
5551
5552 if (m_fade!=FADE_NONE) {
5553 updateFades();
5554 }
5555
5556 if (m_endGameTimer>=0) {
5557 return; // we are just timing down
5558 }
5559
5560 if (TheScriptActions) {
5561 TheScriptActions->update();
5562 }
5563 if (TheScriptConditions) {
5564 TheScriptConditions->update();
5565 }
5566 // Update any countdown timers.
5567 Int i;
5568 // Note - counters start at 1. 0 means not assigned.
5569 for (i=1; i<m_numCounters; i++) {
5570 if (m_counters[i].isCountdownTimer) {
5571 // If counter has any time left, decrement. Counters go to -1 and stop.
5572 if (m_counters[i].value >= 0) {
5573 m_counters[i].value--;
5574 }
5575 }
5576 }
5577
5578 // Evaluate the scripts.
5579 for (i=0; i<TheSidesList->getNumSides(); i++) {
5580 m_currentPlayer = ThePlayerList->getNthPlayer(i);
5581 ScriptList *pSL = TheSidesList->getSideInfo(i)->getScriptList();
5582 if (!pSL) continue;
5583 executeScripts(pSL->getScript());
5584 ScriptGroup *pGroup;
5585 for (pGroup = pSL->getScriptGroup(); pGroup; pGroup=pGroup->getNext()) {
5586 if (!pGroup->isActive()) {
5587 continue; // Don't execute inactive groups.
5588 }
5589 if (pGroup->isSubroutine()) {
5590 continue; // Don't execute subroutine groups.
5591 }
5592 executeScripts(pGroup->getScript());
5593 }
5594 m_currentPlayer = NULL;
5595 }
5596
5597 // Reset the entered/exited flag in teams, so the next update sets them
5598 // correctly. Also, execute any team created scripts.
5599 ThePlayerList->updateTeamStates();
5600
5601 // Clear the UI Interaction flags.
5602 m_uiInteractions.clear();
5603
5604 // update all sequential stuff.
5605 evaluateAndProgressAllSequentialScripts();
5606
5607 // Script debugger stuff
5608 st_CurrentFrame++;
5609 if (st_DebugDLL) {
5610 for (int j = 1; j < m_numCounters; ++j) {
5611 _adjustVariable(m_counters[j].name.str(), m_counters[j].value);
5612 }
5613
5614 for (int k = 1; k < m_numFlags; ++k) {
5615 _adjustVariable(m_flags[k].name.str(), m_flags[k].value);
5616 }
5617 }
5618#ifdef _DEBUG
5619 if (TheGameLogic->getFrame()==0) {
5620 for (i=0; i<m_numAttackInfo; i++) {
5621 m_attackPriorityInfo[i].dumpPriorityInfo();
5622 }
5623 }
5624#endif
5625
5626#ifdef SPECIAL_SCRIPT_PROFILING
5627#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
5628 QueryPerformanceCounter((LARGE_INTEGER *)&endTime64);//LORENZEN'S NOTE_TO_SELF: USE THIS
5629 timeToUpdate = ((double)(endTime64-startTime64) / (double)(freq64));//LORENZEN'S NOTE_TO_SELF: USE THIS
5630 m_numFrames++;
5631 m_totalUpdateTime+=timeToUpdate;
5632 if (timeToUpdate > m_maxUpdateTime) m_maxUpdateTime = timeToUpdate;
5633 m_curUpdateTime = timeToUpdate;
5634#endif
5635#endif
5636
5637#ifdef DO_VTUNE_STUFF
5638 _updateVTune();
5639#endif
5640
5641} // end update
5642
5643//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5645//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5646AsciiString ScriptEngine::getStats(Real *curTimePtr, Real *script1Time, Real *script2Time)
5647{
5648 *curTimePtr = 0;
5649 *script1Time = 0;
5650 *script2Time = 0;
5651 AsciiString msg = "Script Engine Profiling disabled.";
5652#ifdef SPECIAL_SCRIPT_PROFILING
5653#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
5654 msg = "#1-";
5655 *curTimePtr = (Real)m_curUpdateTime;
5656 Int numToDump;
5657 Int i;
5658 if (TheSidesList) {
5659 for (numToDump=0; numToDump<2; numToDump++) {
5660 Real maxTime = 0;
5661 Script *maxScript = NULL;
5662 /* Run through scripts & set condition team names. */
5663 for (i=0; i<TheSidesList->getNumSides(); i++) {
5664 ScriptList *pSL = TheSidesList->getSideInfo(i)->getScriptList();
5665 if (!pSL) continue;
5666 if (pSL == NULL) continue;
5667 Script *pScr;
5668 for (pScr = pSL->getScript(); pScr; pScr=pScr->getNext()) {
5669 if (pScr->getCurTime()>maxTime) {
5670 maxTime = pScr->getCurTime();
5671 maxScript = pScr;
5672 }
5673 }
5674 ScriptGroup *pGroup;
5675 for (pGroup = pSL->getScriptGroup(); pGroup; pGroup=pGroup->getNext()) {
5676 for (pScr = pGroup->getScript(); pScr; pScr=pScr->getNext()) {
5677 if (pScr->getCurTime()>maxTime) {
5678 maxTime = pScr->getCurTime();
5679 maxScript = pScr;
5680 }
5681 }
5682 }
5683 }
5684 if (maxScript) {
5685 if (numToDump == 0) {
5686 *script1Time = maxTime;
5687 } else {
5688 *script2Time = maxTime;
5689 msg.concat(", #2-");
5690 }
5691 msg.concat(maxScript->getName());
5692 maxScript->setCurTime(0); // reset to 0.
5693 }
5694 }
5695 }
5696#endif
5697#endif
5698 return msg;
5699} // end getStats

5725//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5727//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5728void ScriptEngine::updateFades( void )
5729{
5730 m_curFadeFrame++;
5731 Int fade = m_curFadeFrame;
5732 Real factor;
5733 if (fade<=m_fadeFramesIncrease) {
5734 factor = (Real)m_curFadeFrame/m_fadeFramesIncrease;
5735 m_curFadeValue = m_minFade + factor*(m_maxFade-m_minFade);
5736 return;
5737 }
5738 fade -= m_fadeFramesIncrease;
5739 if (fade<=m_fadeFramesHold) {
5740 m_curFadeValue = m_maxFade;
5741 return;
5742 }
5743 fade -= m_fadeFramesHold;
5744 if (fade<=m_fadeFramesDecrease) {
5745 Int divisor = m_fadeFramesDecrease+1;
5746 if (divisor==0) divisor = 1;
5747 factor = (Real)fade/divisor;
5748 m_curFadeValue = m_maxFade + factor*(m_minFade-m_maxFade);
5749 return;
5750 }
5751 // time is up.
5752 m_fade = FADE_NONE;
5753} // end updateFades

5800//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5802//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5803Player *ScriptEngine::getSkirmishEnemyPlayer(void)
5804{
5805 Bool is_GeneralsChallengeContext = TheCampaignManager->getCurrentCampaign() && TheCampaignManager->getCurrentCampaign()->m_isChallengeCampaign;
5806 if (m_currentPlayer) {
5807 Player *enemy = m_currentPlayer->getCurrentEnemy();
5808 if (enemy==NULL) {
5809 // get the human player.
5810 Int i;
5811 for (i=0; i<ThePlayerList->getPlayerCount(); i++) {
5812 enemy = ThePlayerList->getNthPlayer(i);
5813 if (/*enemy->isLocalPlayer() &&*/ enemy->getPlayerType()==PLAYER_HUMAN) {
5814 if (is_GeneralsChallengeContext && enemy->getPlayerNameKey() == NAMEKEY(THE_PLAYER)) {
5815 continue; // In generals challenge, ThePlayer is a dummy player. jba. [8/15/2003]
5816 }
5817
5818 return enemy;
5819 }
5820 enemy = NULL;
5821 }
5822 }
5823 return enemy;
5824 }
5825 DEBUG_CRASH(("No enemy found. Unexpected but not fatal. jba."));
5826 return NULL;
5827}

5829//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5831//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5832Player *ScriptEngine::getPlayerFromAsciiString(const AsciiString& playerString)
5833{
5834 Bool is_GeneralsChallengeContext = TheCampaignManager->getCurrentCampaign() && TheCampaignManager->getCurrentCampaign()->m_isChallengeCampaign;
5835 if (playerString == LOCAL_PLAYER || (playerString == THE_PLAYER && is_GeneralsChallengeContext))
5836 // Designers have built their Generals' Challenge maps, referencing "ThePlayer" meaning the local player.
5837 // However, they've also built many of their single player maps with this string, where "ThePlayer" is not intended as an alias.
5838 return ThePlayerList->getLocalPlayer();
5839 if (playerString == THIS_PLAYER)
5840 return getCurrentPlayer();
5841 else if (playerString == THIS_PLAYER_ENEMY) {
5842 return getSkirmishEnemyPlayer();
5843 }
5844 else {
5845 NameKeyType key = NAMEKEY(playerString);
5846 Player *pPlayer = ThePlayerList->findPlayerWithNameKey(key);
5847 if (pPlayer!=NULL) {
5848 return pPlayer;
5849 }
5850 }
5851
5852 AppendDebugMessage("***Invalid Player name:***", false);
5853
5854 return NULL;
5855}

5860ObjectTypes *ScriptEngine::getObjectTypes(const AsciiString& objectTypeList)
5861{
5862 AllObjectTypesIt it;
5863
5864 for (it = m_allObjectTypeLists.begin(); it != m_allObjectTypeLists.end(); ++it) {
5865 if ((*it) == NULL) {
5866 DEBUG_CRASH(("NULL object type list was unexpected. jkmcd"));
5867 continue;
5868 }
5869
5870 if ((*it)->getListName() == objectTypeList) {
5871 return (*it);
5872 }
5873 }
5874
5875 return NULL;
5876}

5878//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5882//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5883void ScriptEngine::doObjectTypeListMaintenance(const AsciiString& objectTypeList, const AsciiString& objectType, Bool addObject)
5884{
5885 ObjectTypes *currentObjectTypeVec = getObjectTypes(objectTypeList);
5886
5887 if (!currentObjectTypeVec) {
5888 ObjectTypes *newVec = newInstance(ObjectTypes)(objectTypeList);
5889 m_allObjectTypeLists.push_back(newVec);
5890 currentObjectTypeVec = newVec;
5891 }
5892
5893 if (addObject) {
5894 currentObjectTypeVec->addObjectType(objectType);
5895 } else {
5896 currentObjectTypeVec->removeObjectType(objectType);
5897 }
5898
5899 // Remove it. Its dead Jim.
5900 if (currentObjectTypeVec->getListSize() == 0) {
5901 removeObjectTypes(currentObjectTypeVec);
5902
5903 // Semantic emphasis
5904 currentObjectTypeVec = NULL;
5905 }
5906}

5908//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5911//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5912PolygonTrigger *ScriptEngine::getQualifiedTriggerAreaByName( AsciiString name )
5913{
5914 if (name == MY_INNER_PERIMETER || name == MY_OUTER_PERIMETER) {
5915 if (m_currentPlayer) {
5916 Int ndx = m_currentPlayer->getMpStartIndex()+1;
5917 if (name==MY_INNER_PERIMETER) {
5918 name.format("%s%d", INNER_PERIMETER, ndx);
5919 } else {
5920 name.format("%s%d", OUTER_PERIMETER, ndx);
5921 }
5922 } else {
5923 return NULL;
5924 }
5925 } else if (name == ENEMY_INNER_PERIMETER || name == ENEMY_OUTER_PERIMETER) {
5926
5927 Int mpNdx;
5928 mpNdx = -1;
5929 if (m_currentPlayer) {
5930 Player *enemy = getCurrentPlayer()->getCurrentEnemy();
5931 if (enemy) {
5932 mpNdx = enemy->getMpStartIndex()+1;
5933 }
5934 }
5935 if (name==ENEMY_INNER_PERIMETER) {
5936 name.format("%s%d", INNER_PERIMETER, mpNdx);
5937 } else {
5938 name.format("%s%d", OUTER_PERIMETER, mpNdx);
5939 }
5940 }
5941 PolygonTrigger *trig = TheTerrainLogic->getTriggerAreaByName(name);
5942 if (trig==NULL) {
5943 AsciiString msg = "!!!WARNING!!! Trigger area '";
5944 msg.concat(name);
5945 msg.concat("' not found.");
5946 AppendDebugMessage(msg, TRUE);
5947 }
5948
5949 return trig;
5950}

5954//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5956//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5957Team * ScriptEngine::getTeamNamed(const AsciiString& teamName)
5958{
5959 Bool is_GeneralsChallengeContext = TheCampaignManager->getCurrentCampaign() && TheCampaignManager->getCurrentCampaign()->m_isChallengeCampaign;
5960 if (teamName == TEAM_THE_PLAYER && is_GeneralsChallengeContext)
5961 // Designers have built their Generals' Challenge maps, referencing "teamThePlayer" meaning the local player's default (parent) team.
5962 // However, they've also built many of their single player maps with this string, where "teamThePlayer" is not intended as an alias.
5963 return ThePlayerList->getLocalPlayer()->getDefaultTeam();
5964 if (teamName == THIS_TEAM) {
5965 if (m_callingTeam)
5966 return m_callingTeam;
5967 return m_conditionTeam;
5968 }
5969 if (m_callingTeam && m_callingTeam->getName() == teamName) {
5970 return m_callingTeam;
5971 }
5972 if (m_conditionTeam && m_conditionTeam->getName() == teamName) {
5973 return m_conditionTeam;
5974 }
5975 TeamPrototype *theTeamProto = TheTeamFactory->findTeamPrototype( teamName );
5976 if (theTeamProto == NULL) return NULL;
5977 if (theTeamProto->getIsSingleton()) {
5978 Team *theTeam = theTeamProto->getFirstItemIn_TeamInstanceList();
5979 if (theTeam && theTeam->isActive()) {
5980 return theTeam;
5981 }
5982 return NULL; // team wasn't active.
5983 }
5984
5985 static int warnCount = 0;
5986 if (theTeamProto->countTeamInstances()>1) {
5987 if (warnCount<10) {
5988 warnCount++;
5989 AppendDebugMessage("***Referencing multiple team by unspecific instance:***", false);
5990 AppendDebugMessage(teamName, false);
5991 }
5992 }
5993 return theTeamProto->getFirstItemIn_TeamInstanceList();
5994} // end getTeamNamed

6029//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6031//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6032void ScriptEngine::runScript(const AsciiString& scriptName, Team *pThisTeam)
6033{
6034 if (scriptName.isEmpty()) {
6035 return; // no script, just return.
6036 }
6037 if (scriptName==NONE_STRING) {
6038 return; // no script
6039 }
6040
6041
6042 Player *savPlayer = m_currentPlayer;
6043// Team *pSavConditionTeam = m_conditionTeam;
6044 LatchRestore<Team *> latch(m_callingTeam, pThisTeam);
6045
6046 m_conditionTeam = NULL;
6047 m_currentPlayer = NULL;
6048 if (m_callingTeam) {
6049 m_currentPlayer = m_callingTeam->getControllingPlayer();
6050 }
6051 Script *pScript = NULL;
6052 ScriptGroup *pGroup = findGroup(scriptName);
6053 if (pGroup) {
6054 if (pGroup->isSubroutine()) {
6055 if (pGroup->isActive()) {
6056 executeScripts(pGroup->getScript());
6057 }
6058 } else {
6059 AppendDebugMessage("***Attempting to call script that is not a subroutine:***", false);
6060 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6061 DEBUG_LOG(("Attempting to call script '%s' that is not a subroutine.\n", scriptName.str()));
6062 }
6063 } else {
6064 pScript = findScript(scriptName);
6065 if (pScript != NULL) {
6066 if (pScript->isSubroutine()) {
6067 executeScript(pScript);
6068 } else {
6069 AppendDebugMessage("***Attempting to call script that is not a subroutine:***", false);
6070 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6071 DEBUG_LOG(("Attempting to call script '%s' that is not a subroutine.\n", scriptName.str()));
6072 }
6073 } else {
6074 AppendDebugMessage("***Script not defined:***", false);
6075 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6076 DEBUG_LOG(("WARNING: Script '%s' not defined.\n", scriptName.str()));
6077 }
6078 }
6079 // m_callingTeam is restored automatically via LatchRestore
6080 m_conditionTeam = m_conditionTeam;
6081 m_currentPlayer = savPlayer;
6082} // end runScript
6083
6084
6085//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6087//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6088void ScriptEngine::runObjectScript(const AsciiString& scriptName, Object *pThisObject)
6089{
6090 if (scriptName.isEmpty()) {
6091 return; // no script, just return.
6092 }
6093 if (scriptName==NONE_STRING) {
6094 return; // no script
6095 }
6096 Object *pSavCallingObject = m_callingObject;
6097 m_callingObject = pThisObject;
6098 Script *pScript = NULL;
6099 ScriptGroup *pGroup = findGroup(scriptName);
6100 if (pGroup) {
6101 if (pGroup->isSubroutine()) {
6102 if (pGroup->isActive()) {
6103 executeScripts(pGroup->getScript());
6104 }
6105 } else {
6106 AppendDebugMessage("***Attempting to call script that is not a subroutine:***", false);
6107 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6108 DEBUG_LOG(("Attempting to call script '%s' that is not a subroutine.\n", scriptName.str()));
6109 }
6110 } else {
6111 pScript = findScript(scriptName);
6112 if (pScript != NULL) {
6113 if (pScript->isSubroutine()) {
6114 executeScript(pScript);
6115 } else {
6116 AppendDebugMessage("***Attempting to call script that is not a subroutine:***", false);
6117 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6118 DEBUG_LOG(("Attempting to call script '%s' that is not a subroutine.\n", scriptName.str()));
6119 }
6120 } else {
6121 AppendDebugMessage("***Script not defined:***", false);
6122 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6123 DEBUG_LOG(("WARNING: Script '%s' not defined.\n", scriptName.str()));
6124 }
6125 }
6126 m_callingObject = pSavCallingObject;
6127} // end runScript

6130//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6132//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6133Int ScriptEngine::allocateCounter( const AsciiString& name)
6134{
6135 Int i;
6136 // Note - counters start at 1. 0 means not assigned.
6137 for (i=1; i<m_numCounters; i++) {
6138 if (name==m_counters[i].name) {
6139 return i;
6140 }
6141 }
6142 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(m_numCounters<MAX_COUNTERS, ("Too many counters, failed to make '%s'.\n", name.str()));
6143 if (m_numCounters < MAX_COUNTERS) {
6144 m_counters[m_numCounters].name = name;
6145 i = m_numCounters;
6146 m_numCounters++;
6147 return(i);
6148 }
6149 return 0; // Shouldn't ever happen.
6150}
6151
6152//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6154//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6155const TCounter *ScriptEngine::getCounter(const AsciiString& counterName)
6156{
6157 Int i;
6158 for (i=1; i<m_numCounters; i++)
6159 {
6160 if (counterName == m_counters[i].name)
6161 {
6162 return &(m_counters[i]);
6163 }
6164 }
6165 return NULL;
6166}

6168//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6169void ScriptEngine::createNamedMapReveal(const AsciiString& revealName, const AsciiString& waypointName, Real radiusToReveal, const AsciiString& playerName)
6170{
6171 VecNamedRevealIt it;
6172
6173 // Will fail if there's already one in existence of the same name.
6174 for (it = m_namedReveals.begin(); it != m_namedReveals.end(); ++it) {
6175 if (it->m_revealName == revealName) {
6176 DEBUG_CRASH(("ScriptEngine::createNamedMapReveal: Attempted to redefine named Reveal '%s', so I won't change it.\n", revealName.str()));
6177 return;
6178 }
6179 }
6180
6181 NamedReveal reveal;
6182 reveal.m_playerName = playerName;
6183 reveal.m_radiusToReveal = radiusToReveal;
6184 reveal.m_revealName = revealName;
6185 reveal.m_waypointName = waypointName;
6186
6187 m_namedReveals.push_back(reveal);
6188}
6189//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6190void ScriptEngine::doNamedMapReveal(const AsciiString& revealName)
6191{
6192 VecNamedRevealIt it;
6193
6194 NamedReveal *reveal = NULL;
6195 for (it = m_namedReveals.begin(); it != m_namedReveals.end(); ++it) {
6196 if (it->m_revealName == revealName) {
6197 reveal = &(*it);
6198 break;
6199 }
6200 }
6201
6202 if (!reveal) {
6203 return;
6204 }
6205
6206 Waypoint *way = TheTerrainLogic->getWaypointByName(reveal->m_waypointName);
6207 if (!way) {
6208 return;
6209 }
6210
6211 Player *player = getPlayerFromAsciiString(reveal->m_playerName);
6212 if (!player) {
6213 return;
6214 }
6215
6216 Coord3D pos;
6217 pos = *way->getLocation();
6218
6219 ThePartitionManager->doShroudReveal(pos.x, pos.y, reveal->m_radiusToReveal, player->getPlayerMask());
6220}
6221
6222//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6223void ScriptEngine::undoNamedMapReveal(const AsciiString& revealName)
6224{
6225 VecNamedRevealIt it;
6226
6227 NamedReveal *reveal = NULL;
6228 for (it = m_namedReveals.begin(); it != m_namedReveals.end(); ++it) {
6229 if (it->m_revealName == revealName) {
6230 reveal = &(*it);
6231 break;
6232 }
6233 }
6234
6235 if (!reveal) {
6236 return;
6237 }
6238
6239 Waypoint *way = TheTerrainLogic->getWaypointByName(reveal->m_waypointName);
6240 if (!way) {
6241 return;
6242 }
6243
6244 Player *player = getPlayerFromAsciiString(reveal->m_playerName);
6245 if (!player) {
6246 return;
6247 }
6248
6249 Coord3D pos;
6250 pos = *way->getLocation();
6251
6252 ThePartitionManager->undoShroudReveal(pos.x, pos.y, reveal->m_radiusToReveal, player->getPlayerMask());
6253}

6268//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6270//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6271Int ScriptEngine::allocateFlag( const AsciiString& name)
6272{
6273 Int i;
6274 // Note - flags start at 1. 0 means not assigned.
6275 for (i=1; i<m_numFlags; i++) {
6276 if ((name==m_flags[i].name)) {
6277 return i;
6278 }
6279 }
6280 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(m_numFlags < MAX_FLAGS, ("Too many flags, failed to make '%s'..\n", name.str()));
6281 if (m_numFlags < MAX_FLAGS) {
6282 m_flags[m_numFlags].name = name;
6283 i = m_numFlags;
6284 m_numFlags++;
6285 return(i);
6286 }
6287 return 0; // Shouldn't ever happen.
6288}
6289
6290//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6292//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6293ScriptGroup *ScriptEngine::findGroup(const AsciiString& name)
6294{
6295 Int i;
6296 for (i=0; i<TheSidesList->getNumSides(); i++) {
6297 ScriptList *pSL = TheSidesList->getSideInfo(i)->getScriptList();
6298 if (pSL==NULL) continue;
6299 ScriptGroup *pGroup;
6300 for (pGroup = pSL->getScriptGroup(); pGroup; pGroup=pGroup->getNext()) {
6301 if (pGroup->getName() == name) {
6302 return pGroup;
6303 }
6304 }
6305 }
6306 return 0; // Shouldn't ever happen.
6307}
6308
6309//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6311//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6312Script *ScriptEngine::findScript(const AsciiString& name)
6313{
6314 Int i;
6315 for (i=0; i<TheSidesList->getNumSides(); i++) {
6316 ScriptList *pSL = TheSidesList->getSideInfo(i)->getScriptList();
6317 if (pSL==NULL) continue;
6318 Script *pScr;
6319 for (pScr = pSL->getScript(); pScr; pScr=pScr->getNext()) {
6320 if ((name==pScr->getName())) {
6321 return pScr;
6322 }
6323 }
6324 ScriptGroup *pGroup;
6325 for (pGroup = pSL->getScriptGroup(); pGroup; pGroup=pGroup->getNext()) {
6326 for (pScr = pGroup->getScript(); pScr; pScr=pScr->getNext()) {
6327 if ((name==pScr->getName())) {
6328 return pScr;
6329 }
6330 }
6331 }
6332 }
6333 return 0; // Shouldn't ever happen.
6334}

6336//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6338//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6339Bool ScriptEngine::evaluateCounter( Condition *pCondition )
6340{
6341 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pCondition->getNumParameters() >= 3, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6342 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pCondition->getConditionType() == Condition::COUNTER, ("Wrong condition.\n"));
6343 Int counterNdx = pCondition->getParameter(0)->getInt();
6344 if (counterNdx == 0) {
6345 counterNdx = allocateCounter(pCondition->getParameter(0)->getString());
6346 pCondition->getParameter(0)->friend_setInt(counterNdx);
6347 }
6348 Int value = pCondition->getParameter(2)->getInt();
6349 switch (pCondition->getParameter(1)->getInt()) {
6350 case Parameter::LESS_THAN: return m_counters[counterNdx].value < value;
6351 case Parameter::LESS_EQUAL: return m_counters[counterNdx].value <= value;
6352 case Parameter::EQUAL: return m_counters[counterNdx].value == value;
6353 case Parameter::GREATER_EQUAL: return m_counters[counterNdx].value >= value;
6354 case Parameter::GREATER: return m_counters[counterNdx].value > value;
6355 case Parameter::NOT_EQUAL: return m_counters[counterNdx].value != value;
6356 }
6357 return false;
6358}
6359

6364{
6365 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pAction->getNumParameters() >= 2, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6366 Int counterNdx = pAction->getParameter(0)->getInt();
6367 if (counterNdx == 0) {
6368 counterNdx = allocateCounter(pAction->getParameter(0)->getString());
6369 pAction->getParameter(0)->friend_setInt(counterNdx);
6370 }
6371 Int value = pAction->getParameter(1)->getInt();
6372 m_counters[counterNdx].value = value;
6373}

6375//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6377//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6378void ScriptEngine::setFade( ScriptAction *pAction )
6379{
6380#if defined(_DEBUG) || defined(_INTERNAL)
6381 if (TheGlobalData->m_disableCameraFade)
6382 {
6383 m_fade = FADE_NONE;
6384 return;
6385 }
6386#endif
6387
6388 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pAction->getNumParameters() >= 5, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6389 switch (pAction->getActionType()) {
6390 default: m_fade = FADE_NONE; return;
6391 case ScriptAction::CAMERA_FADE_ADD: m_fade = FADE_ADD; break;
6392 case ScriptAction::CAMERA_FADE_SUBTRACT: m_fade = FADE_SUBTRACT; break;
6393 case ScriptAction::CAMERA_FADE_SATURATE: m_fade = FADE_SATURATE; break;
6394 case ScriptAction::CAMERA_FADE_MULTIPLY: m_fade = FADE_MULTIPLY; break;
6395 }
6396 m_curFadeFrame = 0;
6397 m_minFade = pAction->getParameter(0)->getReal();
6398 m_maxFade = pAction->getParameter(1)->getReal();
6399 m_fadeFramesIncrease = pAction->getParameter(2)->getInt();
6400 m_fadeFramesHold = pAction->getParameter(3)->getInt();
6401 m_fadeFramesDecrease = pAction->getParameter(4)->getInt();
6402 m_curFadeValue = m_minFade;
6403 if( m_fadeFramesIncrease == 0 )
6404 {
6405 updateFades();
6406 }
6407}

6417 m_breezeInfo.m_directionVec.x = Sin(m_breezeInfo.m_direction);
6418 m_breezeInfo.m_directionVec.y = Cos(m_breezeInfo.m_direction);

6423 m_breezeInfo.m_breezePeriod = 1;

6458//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6460//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6461Bool ScriptEngine::evaluateFlag( Condition *pCondition )
6462{
6463 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pCondition->getNumParameters() >= 2, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6464 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pCondition->getConditionType() == Condition::FLAG, ("Wrong condition.\n"));
6465 Int flagNdx = pCondition->getParameter(0)->getInt();
6466 if (flagNdx == 0) {
6467 flagNdx = allocateFlag(pCondition->getParameter(0)->getString());
6468 pCondition->getParameter(0)->friend_setInt(flagNdx);
6469 }
6470 Int value = pCondition->getParameter(1)->getInt();
6471 Bool boolVal = (value!=0);
6472 Bool boolFlag = (m_flags[flagNdx].value != 0);
6473
6474 if (boolVal == boolFlag) {
6475 return true;
6476 }
6477
6478 for (ListAsciiStringIt it = m_uiInteractions.begin(); it != m_uiInteractions.end(); ++it) {
6479 if (it->compare(pCondition->getParameter(0)->getString()) == 0) {
6480 // just return. This flag will be cleared up at the end of the ScriptEngine::update() call
6481 return true;
6482 }
6483 }
6484 return false;
6485}

6506//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6507AttackPriorityInfo * ScriptEngine::findAttackInfo(const AsciiString& name, Bool addIfNotFound)
6508{
6509 // Note - m_attackPriorityInfo[0] is the default info, with an empty name.
6510 Int i;
6511 for (i=1; i<m_numAttackInfo; i++) {
6512 if (m_attackPriorityInfo[i].getName() == name) {
6513 return &m_attackPriorityInfo[i];
6514 }
6515 }
6516 if (addIfNotFound && m_numAttackInfo<MAX_ATTACK_PRIORITIES) {
6517 m_attackPriorityInfo[m_numAttackInfo].friend_setName(name);
6518 m_numAttackInfo++;
6519 return &m_attackPriorityInfo[m_numAttackInfo-1];
6520 }
6521 return NULL;
6522}

6550//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6552//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6553void ScriptEngine::setPriorityThing( ScriptAction *pAction )
6554{
6555 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pAction->getNumParameters() >= 3, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6556
6557 AsciiString typeArgument = pAction->getParameter(1)->getString();
6558
6559 // Our argument could be an individual type, or a list name.
6560 const ObjectTypes *types = TheScriptEngine->getObjectTypes(typeArgument);
6561 if( !types )
6562 {
6563 // Lookup failed, so it is just a single type
6564
6565 const ThingTemplate *thingTemplate;
6566 // get thing template based from map object name
6567 thingTemplate = TheThingFactory->findTemplate(typeArgument);
6568 if (thingTemplate==NULL) {
6569 AppendDebugMessage("***Attempting to set attack priority on an invalid thing:***", false);
6570 AppendDebugMessage(pAction->getParameter(0)->getString(), false);
6571 return;
6572 }
6573 AttackPriorityInfo *info = findAttackInfo(pAction->getParameter(0)->getString(), true);
6574 if (info==NULL) {
6575 AppendDebugMessage("***Error allocating attack priority set - fix or raise limit. ***", false);
6576 return;
6577 }
6578 // DEBUG LOGGING
6579// AsciiString debug = "Set the priority on ";
6580// debug.concat(thingTemplate->getName().str());
6581// debug.concat(" to ");
6582// char intBuffer[16];
6583// itoa(pAction->getParameter(2)->getInt(), intBuffer, 10);
6584// debug.concat(intBuffer);
6585// AppendDebugMessage(debug, false);
6586 // END DEBUGGING LOGGING
6587 info->setPriority(thingTemplate, pAction->getParameter(2)->getInt());
6588
6589 return;
6590 }
6591 else
6592 {
6593 // Found a list by this name, so we have a bunch of things
6594
6595 for( Int typeIndex = 0; typeIndex < types->getListSize(); typeIndex ++ )
6596 {
6597 AsciiString thisTypeName = types->getNthInList(typeIndex);
6598 const ThingTemplate *thisType = TheThingFactory->findTemplate(thisTypeName);
6599 if (thisType==NULL) {
6600 AppendDebugMessage("***Attempting to set attack priority on an invalid thing:***", false);
6601 AppendDebugMessage(pAction->getParameter(0)->getString(), false);
6602 return;
6603 }
6604 AttackPriorityInfo *info = findAttackInfo(pAction->getParameter(0)->getString(), true);
6605 if (info==NULL) {
6606 AppendDebugMessage("***Error allocating attack priority set - fix or raise limit. ***", false);
6607 return;
6608 }
6609 // DEBUG LOGGING
6610// AsciiString debug = "Set the priority on ";
6611// debug.concat(thisType->getName().str());
6612// debug.concat(" to ");
6613// char intBuffer[16];
6614// itoa(pAction->getParameter(2)->getInt(), intBuffer, 10);
6615// debug.concat(intBuffer);
6616// AppendDebugMessage(debug, false);
6617 // END DEBUGGING LOGGING
6618 info->setPriority(thisType, pAction->getParameter(2)->getInt());
6619 }
6620
6621 return;
6622 }
6623
6624}

6626//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6628//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6629void ScriptEngine::setPriorityKind( ScriptAction *pAction )
6630{
6631 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pAction->getNumParameters() >= 3, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6632 AttackPriorityInfo *info = findAttackInfo(pAction->getParameter(0)->getString(), true);
6633 if (info==NULL) {
6634 AppendDebugMessage("***Error allocating attack priority set - fix or raise limit. ***", false);
6635 return;
6636 }
6637 KindOfType kind = (KindOfType)pAction->getParameter(1)->getInt();
6638 Int priority = pAction->getParameter(2)->getInt();
6639 const ThingTemplate *tTemplate;
6640 for( tTemplate = TheThingFactory->firstTemplate();
6641 tTemplate;
6642 tTemplate = tTemplate->friend_getNextTemplate() )
6643 {
6644 if (tTemplate->isKindOf(kind)) {
6645 info->setPriority(tTemplate, priority);
6646 }
6647 }
6648}

6664//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6665Int ScriptEngine::getObjectCount(Int playerIndex, const AsciiString& objectTypeName) const
6666{
6667 if (!ThePlayerList->getNthPlayer(playerIndex)->isPlayerActive()) {
6668 // Inactive players should always pretend they have 0 objects.
6669 return 0;
6670 }
6671
6672 const ObjectTypeCount &ocm = m_objectCounts[playerIndex];
6673
6674 ObjectTypeCount::const_iterator it = ocm.find(objectTypeName);
6675 if (it == ocm.end()) {
6676 return 0;
6677 }
6678
6679 return it->second;
6680}

6688 ocm[objectTypeName] = newCount;
6689}

6691//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6694//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6695void ScriptEngine::removeObjectTypes(ObjectTypes *typesToRemove)
6696{
6697 if (typesToRemove == NULL) {
6698 return;
6699 }
6700
6701 AllObjectTypesIt it = std::find(m_allObjectTypeLists.begin(), m_allObjectTypeLists.end(), typesToRemove);
6702
6703 if (it == m_allObjectTypeLists.end()) {
6704 // Debug crash maybe?
6705 return;
6706 }
6707
6708 // delete it.
6709 typesToRemove->deleteInstance();
6710
6711 // remove it from the main array of stuff
6712 m_allObjectTypeLists.erase(it);
6713}

6715//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6717//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6718Bool ScriptEngine::evaluateTimer( Condition *pCondition )
6719{
6720 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pCondition->getNumParameters() >= 1, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6721 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pCondition->getConditionType() == Condition::TIMER_EXPIRED, ("Wrong condition.\n"));
6722 Int counterNdx = pCondition->getParameter(0)->getInt();
6723 if (counterNdx == 0) {
6724 counterNdx = allocateCounter(pCondition->getParameter(0)->getString());
6725 pCondition->getParameter(0)->friend_setInt(counterNdx);
6726 }
6727 if (!m_counters[counterNdx].isCountdownTimer) {
6728 return false; // Timer hasn't been started yet.
6729 }
6730 Int value = m_counters[counterNdx].value;
6731 // Timers decrement down to -1.
6732 return (value < 1);
6733}
6734
6735//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6737//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6738void ScriptEngine::setTimer( ScriptAction *pAction, Bool millisecondTimer, Bool random )
6739{
6740 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pAction->getNumParameters() >= 2, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6741 Int counterNdx = pAction->getParameter(0)->getInt();
6742 if (counterNdx == 0) {
6743 counterNdx = allocateCounter(pAction->getParameter(0)->getString());
6744 pAction->getParameter(0)->friend_setInt(counterNdx);
6745 }
6746 if (millisecondTimer) {
6747 Real value = pAction->getParameter(1)->getReal();
6748 if (random) {
6749 Real randomValue = pAction->getParameter(2)->getReal();
6750 value = GameLogicRandomValue(value, randomValue);
6751 }
6752 m_counters[counterNdx].value = REAL_TO_INT_CEIL(ConvertDurationFromMsecsToFrames(value*1000));
6753 } else {
6754 Int value = pAction->getParameter(1)->getInt();
6755 if (random) {
6756 Int randomValue = pAction->getParameter(2)->getInt();
6757 value = GameLogicRandomValue(value, randomValue);
6758 }
6759 m_counters[counterNdx].value = value;
6760 }
6761 m_counters[counterNdx].isCountdownTimer = true;
6762}

6794//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6796//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6797void ScriptEngine::adjustTimer( ScriptAction *pAction, Bool millisecondTimer, Bool add)
6798{
6799 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pAction->getNumParameters() >= 2, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6800 Int counterNdx = pAction->getParameter(1)->getInt();
6801 if (counterNdx == 0) {
6802 counterNdx = allocateCounter(pAction->getParameter(1)->getString());
6803 pAction->getParameter(1)->friend_setInt(counterNdx);
6804 }
6805 if (millisecondTimer) {
6806 Real value = pAction->getParameter(0)->getReal();
6807 if (!add)
6808 value = -value;
6809 m_counters[counterNdx].value += REAL_TO_INT_CEIL(ConvertDurationFromMsecsToFrames(value*1000));
6810 } else {
6811 Int value = pAction->getParameter(0)->getInt();
6812 if (!add)
6813 value = -value;
6814 m_counters[counterNdx].value += value;
6815 }
6816}

6850//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6852//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6853void ScriptEngine::callSubroutine( ScriptAction *pAction )
6854{
6855 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(pAction->getNumParameters() >= 1, ("Not enough parameters.\n"));
6856 AsciiString scriptName = pAction->getParameter(0)->getString();
6857 Script *pScript;
6858 ScriptGroup *pGroup = findGroup(scriptName);
6859 if (pGroup) {
6860 if (pGroup->isSubroutine()) {
6861 if (pGroup->isActive()) {
6862 executeScripts(pGroup->getScript());
6863 }
6864 } else {
6865 AppendDebugMessage("***Attempting to call script that is not a subroutine:***", false);
6866 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6867 DEBUG_LOG(("Attempting to call script '%s' that is not a subroutine.\n", scriptName.str()));
6868 }
6869 } else {
6870 pScript = findScript(scriptName);
6871 if (pScript != NULL) {
6872 if (pScript->isSubroutine()) {
6873 executeScript(pScript);
6874 } else {
6875 AppendDebugMessage("***Attempting to call script that is not a subroutine:***", false);
6876 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6877 DEBUG_LOG(("Attempting to call script '%s' that is not a subroutine.\n", scriptName.str()));
6878 }
6879 } else {
6880 AppendDebugMessage("***Script not defined:***", false);
6881 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6882 DEBUG_LOG(("WARNING: Script '%s' not defined.\n", scriptName.str()));
6883 }
6884 }
6885}
6886
6887//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6890//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6891void ScriptEngine::checkConditionsForTeamNames(Script *pScript)
6892{
6893 AsciiString singletonTeamName;
6894 AsciiString multiTeamName;
6895
6896 if (pScript->getDelayEvalSeconds()>0) {
6897 // Offset by a random number of frames
6898 pScript->setFrameToEvaluate(GameLogicRandomValue(0,2*LOGICFRAMES_PER_SECOND));
6899 } else {
6900 pScript->setFrameToEvaluate(0);
6901 }
6902
6903 AsciiString scriptName = pScript->getName();
6904 OrCondition *pOr;
6905 for (pOr = pScript->getOrCondition(); pOr; pOr = pOr->getNextOrCondition()) {
6906 Condition *pCondition;
6907 for (pCondition = pOr->getFirstAndCondition(); pCondition; pCondition = pCondition->getNext()) {
6908 Int i;
6909 for (i=0; i<pCondition->getNumParameters(); i++) {
6910 if (Parameter::TEAM == pCondition->getParameter(i)->getParameterType()) {
6911 AsciiString teamName = pCondition->getParameter(i)->getString();
6912 TeamPrototype *proto = TheTeamFactory->findTeamPrototype(teamName);
6913 if (proto==NULL) continue; // Undefined team - don't bother.
6914 Bool singleton = proto->getIsSingleton();
6915 if (proto->getTemplateInfo()->m_maxInstances < 2) {
6916 singleton = true;
6917 }
6918 if (singleton) {
6919 singletonTeamName = teamName; // Singleton team - use if it is the only one, but can have multiple of these.
6920 } else {
6921 if (multiTeamName.isEmpty()) {
6922 multiTeamName = teamName; // Use one multiply defined team. Good.
6923 } else if (multiTeamName!=teamName) {
6924 // More than one multiply defined team - bad.
6925 AppendDebugMessage("***WARNING: Script contains multiple non-singleton team conditions::***", false);
6926 AppendDebugMessage(scriptName, false);
6927 AppendDebugMessage(multiTeamName, false);
6928 AppendDebugMessage(teamName, false);
6929 DEBUG_LOG(("WARNING: Script '%s' contains multiple non-singleton team conditions: %s & %s.\n", scriptName.str(),
6930 multiTeamName.str(), teamName.str()));
6931 }
6932 }
6933 }
6934 }
6935 }
6936 }
6937 if (multiTeamName.isEmpty()) {
6938 if (!singletonTeamName.isEmpty()) {
6939 pScript->setConditionTeamName(singletonTeamName);
6940 }
6941 } else {
6942 pScript->setConditionTeamName(multiTeamName);
6943 }
6944
6945}
6946
6947//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6949//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6950void ScriptEngine::executeScript( Script *pScript )
6951{
6952
6953 pScript->setCurTime(0);
6954 // If script is not active, return.
6955 if (!pScript->isActive()) {
6956 return;
6957 }
6958 enum GameDifficulty difficulty = getGlobalDifficulty();
6959 if (m_currentPlayer) {
6960 difficulty = m_currentPlayer->getPlayerDifficulty();
6961 }
6962 // If script doesn't match difficulty level, return.
6963 switch (difficulty) {
6964 case DIFFICULTY_EASY : if (!pScript->isEasy()) return; break;
6965 case DIFFICULTY_NORMAL : if (!pScript->isNormal()) return; break;
6966 case DIFFICULTY_HARD : if (!pScript->isHard()) return; break;
6967 }
6968 // If we are doing peridic evaluation, check the frame.
6969 if (TheGameLogic->getFrame()<pScript->getFrameToEvaluate()) {
6970 return;
6971 }
6972 Int delaySeconds = pScript->getDelayEvalSeconds();
6973
6974 if (delaySeconds>0) {
6975 pScript->setFrameToEvaluate(TheGameLogic->getFrame()+delaySeconds*LOGICFRAMES_PER_SECOND);
6976 }
6977#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
6978#ifdef SPECIAL_SCRIPT_PROFILING
6979 __int64 startTime64;
6980 Real timeToEvaluate=0.0f;
6981 __int64 endTime64,freq64;
6982 QueryPerformanceFrequency((LARGE_INTEGER *)&freq64);
6983 QueryPerformanceCounter((LARGE_INTEGER *)&startTime64);
6984#endif
6985#endif
6986
6987 Team *pSavConditionTeam = m_conditionTeam;
6988 TeamPrototype *pProto = NULL;
6989
6990 if (!pScript->getConditionTeamName().isEmpty()) {
6991 pProto = TheTeamFactory->findTeamPrototype(pScript->getConditionTeamName());
6992 }
6993
6994 if (pProto && pProto->countTeamInstances() > 0) {
6995 // We have a team referred to in the conditions. Iterate over the instances of the team,
6996 // applying the script conditions (and possibly actions) to each instance of the team.
6997 for (DLINK_ITERATOR<Team> iter = pProto->iterate_TeamInstanceList(); !iter.done(); iter.advance()) {
6998 m_conditionTeam = iter.cur();
6999 // If conditions evaluate to true, execute actions.
7000 if (evaluateConditions(pScript)) {
7001 // Script Debug window
7002 if (pScript->getAction()) {
7003 _appendMessage(pScript->getName());
7004 executeActions(pScript->getAction());
7005 }
7006
7007 if (pScript->isOneShot()) {
7008 pScript->setActive(false);
7009 }
7010 } else if (pScript->getFalseAction()) {
7011
7012 // Script Debug window
7013 _appendMessage(pScript->getName(), false);
7014
7015 // Only do this is there are actually false actions.
7016 executeActions(pScript->getFalseAction());
7017 }
7018 }
7019
7020 } else {
7021 m_conditionTeam = NULL;
7022 // If conditions evaluate to true, execute actions.
7023 if (evaluateConditions(pScript)) {
7024 if (pScript->getAction()) {
7025 // Script Debug window
7026 _appendMessage(pScript->getName());
7027 executeActions(pScript->getAction());
7028 }
7029
7030 if (pScript->isOneShot()) {
7031 pScript->setActive(false);
7032 }
7033 } else if (pScript->getFalseAction()) {
7034
7035 // Script Debug window
7036 _appendMessage(pScript->getName(), false);
7037
7038 // Only do this is there are actually false actions.
7039 executeActions(pScript->getFalseAction());
7040 if (pScript->isOneShot()) {
7041 pScript->setActive(false);
7042 }
7043 }
7044 }
7045#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
7046#ifdef SPECIAL_SCRIPT_PROFILING
7047 QueryPerformanceCounter((LARGE_INTEGER *)&endTime64);
7048 timeToEvaluate = ((Real)(endTime64-startTime64) / (Real)(freq64));
7049 pScript->setCurTime(timeToEvaluate);
7050#endif
7051#endif
7052
7053 m_conditionTeam = pSavConditionTeam;
7054}
7055
7056//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7058//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7059Bool ScriptEngine::evaluateCondition( Condition *pCondition )
7060{
7061 switch (pCondition->getConditionType()) {
7062 default:
7063 return TheScriptConditions->evaluateCondition(pCondition);
7064 case Condition::CONDITION_FALSE: return false;
7065 case Condition::CONDITION_TRUE: return true;
7066 case Condition::COUNTER: return evaluateCounter(pCondition);
7067 case Condition::FLAG: return evaluateFlag(pCondition);
7068 case Condition::TIMER_EXPIRED: return evaluateTimer(pCondition);
7069 }
7070}
7071
7072//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7074//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7075void ScriptEngine::friend_executeAction( ScriptAction *pActionHead, Team *pThisTeam )
7076{
7077 Team *pSavCallingTeam = m_callingTeam;
7078 Player *pSavPlayer = m_currentPlayer;
7079 m_callingTeam = pThisTeam;
7080 m_currentPlayer = NULL;
7081 if (pThisTeam) {
7082 m_currentPlayer = pThisTeam->getControllingPlayer();
7083 }
7084 executeActions(pActionHead);
7085 m_callingTeam = pSavCallingTeam;
7086 m_currentPlayer = pSavPlayer;
7087}
7088
7089//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7091//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7092void ScriptEngine::addObjectToCache(Object* pNewObject)
7093{
7094 if (!pNewObject) {
7095 return;
7096 }
7097
7098 AsciiString objName = pNewObject->getName();
7099
7100 if (objName == AsciiString::TheEmptyString) {
7101 return;
7102 }
7103
7104 for (VecNamedRequestsIt it = m_namedObjects.begin(); it != m_namedObjects.end(); ++it) {
7105 if (it->first == objName) {
7106 if (it->second == NULL) {
7107 AsciiString newNameForDead;
7108 newNameForDead.format("Reassigning dead object's name '%s' to object (%d) of type '%s'\n", objName.str(), pNewObject->getID(), pNewObject->getTemplate()->getName().str());
7109 TheScriptEngine->AppendDebugMessage(newNameForDead, FALSE);
7110 DEBUG_LOG((newNameForDead.str()));
7111 it->second = pNewObject;
7112 return;
7113 } else {
7114 DEBUG_CRASH(("Attempting to assign the name '%s' to object (%d) of type '%s',"
7115 " but object (%d) of type '%s' already has that name\n",
7116 objName.str(), pNewObject->getID(), pNewObject->getTemplate()->getName().str(),
7117 it->second->getID(), it->second->getTemplate()->getName().str()));
7118 return;
7119 }
7120 }
7121
7122 if (pNewObject == (it->second)) {
7123 it->first = objName;
7124 return;
7125 }
7126 }
7127
7128 NamedRequest req;
7129 req.first = objName;
7130 req.second = pNewObject;
7131
7132 m_namedObjects.push_back(req);
7133}
7134
7135//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7137//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7138void ScriptEngine::removeObjectFromCache( Object* pDeadObject )
7139{
7140 for (VecNamedRequestsIt it = m_namedObjects.begin(); it != m_namedObjects.end(); ++it) {
7141 if (pDeadObject == (it->second)) {
7142 it->second = NULL; // Don't remove it, cause we want to check whether we ever knew a name later
7143 break;
7144 }
7145 }
7146}
7147
7148//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7155//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7156void ScriptEngine::transferObjectName( const AsciiString& unitName, Object *pNewObject )
7157{
7158 //Sanity checks
7159 if( !pNewObject || !unitName.getLength() )
7160 {
7161 return;
7162 }
7163
7164 //John Ahlquist: When transferring an object name, make sure the new object isn't already in
7165 // the vector. If so, remove it, or it'll end up there twice and cause a crash.
7166 if( pNewObject->getName().isNotEmpty() )
7167 {
7168 removeObjectFromCache(pNewObject);
7169 }
7170
7171 pNewObject->setName(unitName); // make sure it's named the name.
7172
7173 //Loop through the cached list and find the string entry. If found, change the object
7174 //so it's pointing to the new one.
7175 for( VecNamedRequestsIt it = m_namedObjects.begin(); it != m_namedObjects.end(); ++it )
7176 {
7177 if( !unitName.compare( it->first ) )
7178 {
7179 Object* pOldObj = it->second;
7180 if( pOldObj )
7181 {
7182 // if you are transferring your name, you should also transfer any custom indicator color you have.
7183 if (pOldObj->hasCustomIndicatorColor())
7184 pNewObject->setCustomIndicatorColor(pOldObj->getIndicatorColor());
7185 else
7186 pNewObject->removeCustomIndicatorColor();
7187 }
7188
7189 it->second = pNewObject;
7190
7191 return;
7192 }
7193 }
7194
7195}
7196
7197//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7198//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7199void ScriptEngine::notifyOfObjectDestruction( Object *pDeadObject )
7200{
7201 if (!pDeadObject->getName().isEmpty())
7202 {
7203 removeObjectFromCache(pDeadObject);
7204 }
7205
7206 if (m_conditionObject == pDeadObject) {
7207 m_conditionObject = NULL;
7208 }
7209
7210 if (m_callingObject == pDeadObject) {
7211 m_callingObject = NULL;
7212 }
7213}

7289//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7291//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7292Bool ScriptEngine::isSpeechComplete( const AsciiString& testSpeech, Bool removeFromList )
7293{
7294 ListAsciiStringUINTIt findIt;
7295 for (findIt = m_testingSpeech.begin(); findIt != m_testingSpeech.end(); ++findIt) {
7296 if (findIt->first == testSpeech) {
7297 break;
7298 }
7299 }
7300
7301 if (findIt == m_testingSpeech.end()) {
7302 PairAsciiStringUINT newPair;
7303 AudioEventRTS event(testSpeech);
7304 Real audioLength = TheAudio->getAudioLengthMS(&event);
7305 UnsignedInt frameCount = REAL_TO_UNSIGNEDINT(audioLength / MSEC_PER_LOGICFRAME_REAL);
7306
7307 newPair.first = testSpeech;
7308 newPair.second = frameCount + TheGameLogic->getFrame();
7309 m_testingSpeech.push_front(newPair);
7310 findIt = m_testingSpeech.begin();
7311 }
7312
7313 if (TheGameLogic->getFrame() >= findIt->second) {
7314 // This audio is completed
7315 if (removeFromList) {
7316 m_testingSpeech.erase(findIt);
7317 }
7318 return true;
7319 }
7320
7321 return false;
7322}

7362Bool ScriptEngine::isSpecialPowerTriggered( Int playerIndex, const AsciiString& completedPower, Bool removeFromList, ObjectID sourceObj )
7363{
7364 if (playerIndex < 0 || playerIndex >= MAX_PLAYER_COUNT)
7365 return FALSE;
7366
7367 ListAsciiStringObjectID *specialList = &(m_triggeredSpecialPowers[playerIndex]);
7368
7369 for (ListAsciiStringObjectIDIt findIt = specialList->begin(); findIt != specialList->end(); ++findIt)
7370 {
7371 AsciiStringObjectIDPair pair = *findIt;
7372 if (pair.first == completedPower && (sourceObj == INVALID_ID || sourceObj == pair.second))
7373 {
7374 if (removeFromList) {
7375 specialList->erase(findIt);
7376 }
7377 return TRUE;
7378 }
7379 }
7380
7381 return FALSE;
7382}
