7511//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7514//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7515void ScriptEngine::setToppleDirection( const AsciiString& objectName, const Coord3D *direction )
7516{
7517 if (objectName.isEmpty()) {
7518 return;
7519 }
7520
7521 ListAsciiStringCoord3DIt it;
7522 for (it = m_toppleDirections.begin(); it != m_toppleDirections.end(); ++it) {
7523 if (it->first == objectName) {
7524 if (direction) {
7525 it->second = *direction;
7526 } else {
7527 m_toppleDirections.erase(it);
7528 }
7529 return;
7530 }
7531 }
7532
7533 AsciiStringCoord3DPair newPair;
7534 newPair.first = objectName;
7535 newPair.second = (*direction);
7536 m_toppleDirections.push_front(newPair);
7537}
7538
7539//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7542//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7543void ScriptEngine::adjustToppleDirection( Object *object, Coord2D *direction)
7544{
7545 if (!(object && direction)) {
7546 return;
7547 }
7548
7549 Coord3D dir;
7550 dir.x = (*direction).x;
7551 dir.y = (*direction).y;
7552 adjustToppleDirection(object, &dir);
7553 (*direction).x = dir.x;
7554 (*direction).y = dir.y;
7555}
7556
7557//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7560//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7561void ScriptEngine::adjustToppleDirection( Object *object, Coord3D *direction)
7562{
7563 AsciiString objName = object->getName();
7564 if (objName.isEmpty() || !direction) {
7565 return;
7566 }
7567
7568 // this one *MAY* have a specified topple direction
7569 ListAsciiStringCoord3DIt it;
7570 for (it = m_toppleDirections.begin(); it != m_toppleDirections.end(); ++it) {
7571 if (it->first == objName) {
7572 (*direction) = it->second;
7573 (*direction).normalize();
7574 return;
7575 }
7576 }
7577}
7578
7579//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7581//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7582Bool ScriptEngine::evaluateConditions( Script *pScript, Team *thisTeam, Player *player )
7583{
7584 LatchRestore<Team*> latch(m_callingTeam, thisTeam);
7585 if (thisTeam) player = thisTeam->getControllingPlayer();
7586 if (player==NULL) player=m_currentPlayer;
7587 LatchRestore<Player*> latch2(m_currentPlayer, player);
7588 OrCondition *pConditionHead = pScript->getOrCondition();
7589 Bool testValue = false;
7590
7591#ifdef DEBUG_LOGGING
7592#define COLLECT_CONDITION_EVAL_TIMES
7593#endif
7594#ifdef COLLECT_CONDITION_EVAL_TIMES
7595 __int64 startTime64;
7596 Real timeToEvaluate=0.0f;
7597 __int64 endTime64,freq64;
7598 QueryPerformanceFrequency((LARGE_INTEGER *)&freq64);
7599 QueryPerformanceCounter((LARGE_INTEGER *)&startTime64);
7600#endif
7601 OrCondition *pCurCondition;
7602 for (pCurCondition = pConditionHead; pCurCondition; pCurCondition = pCurCondition->getNextOrCondition()) {
7603 Condition *pCondition = pCurCondition->getFirstAndCondition();
7604 if (!pCondition) continue; // No conditions, so go to the next or.
7605 Bool andTerm = true;
7606 while (pCondition && andTerm) {
7607 if (!evaluateCondition(pCondition)) {
7608 andTerm = false;
7609 break; // Short circuit the and evauation - after the first false, we can quit.
7610 }
7611 pCondition = pCondition->getNext();
7612 }
7613 if (andTerm) { // The outer list is OR'ed - so any true inner means we are true.
7614 testValue = true;
7615 break;
7616 }
7617 }
7618#ifdef COLLECT_CONDITION_EVAL_TIMES
7619 QueryPerformanceCounter((LARGE_INTEGER *)&endTime64);
7620 timeToEvaluate = ((Real)(endTime64-startTime64) / (Real)(freq64));
7621 pScript->incrementConditionCount();
7622 pScript->addToConditionTime(timeToEvaluate);
7623#endif
7624
7625 return testValue; // If none of the or's fired, then it is false.
7626}
7627
7628
7629
7630//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7632//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7633void ScriptEngine::executeActions( ScriptAction *pActionHead )
7634{
7635 ScriptAction *pCurAction;
7636 UnicodeString uStr1;
7637 for (pCurAction = pActionHead; pCurAction; pCurAction = pCurAction->getNext()) {
7638 switch (pCurAction->getActionType()) {
7639 default: if (TheScriptActions) TheScriptActions->executeAction(pCurAction); break;
7640 case ScriptAction::SET_COUNTER: setCounter(pCurAction); break;
7641 case ScriptAction::SET_TREE_SWAY: setSway(pCurAction); break;
7642 case ScriptAction::INCREMENT_COUNTER: addCounter(pCurAction); break;
7643 case ScriptAction::DECREMENT_COUNTER: subCounter(pCurAction); break;
7644 case ScriptAction::SET_FLAG: setFlag(pCurAction);break;
7645 case ScriptAction::STOP_TIMER: pauseTimer(pCurAction);break;
7646 case ScriptAction::RESTART_TIMER: restartTimer(pCurAction);break;
7647 case ScriptAction::SET_TIMER: setTimer(pCurAction, false, false);break;
7648 case ScriptAction::SET_MILLISECOND_TIMER: setTimer(pCurAction, true, false);break;
7649 case ScriptAction::SET_RANDOM_TIMER: setTimer(pCurAction, false, true);break;
7650 case ScriptAction::SET_RANDOM_MSEC_TIMER: setTimer(pCurAction, true, true);break;
7651 case ScriptAction::ADD_TO_MSEC_TIMER: adjustTimer(pCurAction, true, true);break;
7652 case ScriptAction::SUB_FROM_MSEC_TIMER: adjustTimer(pCurAction, true, false);break;
7653 case ScriptAction::ENABLE_SCRIPT: enableScript(pCurAction);break;
7654 case ScriptAction::DISABLE_SCRIPT: disableScript(pCurAction);break;
7655 case ScriptAction::CALL_SUBROUTINE: callSubroutine(pCurAction);break;
7656
7657 // Fade operations.
7658 case ScriptAction::CAMERA_FADE_ADD :
7659 case ScriptAction::CAMERA_FADE_SUBTRACT :
7660 case ScriptAction::CAMERA_FADE_SATURATE :
7661 case ScriptAction::CAMERA_FADE_MULTIPLY :
7662 setFade(pCurAction); break;
7663
7664 // Attack priority set operations.
7665 case ScriptAction::SET_ATTACK_PRIORITY_THING : setPriorityThing(pCurAction); break;
7666 case ScriptAction::SET_ATTACK_PRIORITY_KIND_OF : setPriorityKind(pCurAction); break;
7667 case ScriptAction::SET_DEFAULT_ATTACK_PRIORITY : setPriorityDefault(pCurAction); break;
7668
7669 case ScriptAction::NO_OP: /* just break. */; break;
7670 }
7671 }
7672}
7673
7674//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7676//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7677void ScriptEngine::executeScripts( Script *pScriptHead )
7678{
7679
7680 // Evaluate the scripts.
7681 Script *pCurScript;
7682 for (pCurScript = pScriptHead; pCurScript; pCurScript=pCurScript->getNext()) {
7683 if (pCurScript->isSubroutine()) {
7684 continue; // Don't execute subroutines, except when called by other scripts.
7685 }
7686 executeScript(pCurScript);
7687 }
7688} // end update
7689
7690
7691//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7693//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7694const ActionTemplate * ScriptEngine::getActionTemplate( Int ndx )
7695{
7696 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(ndx >= 0 && ndx < ScriptAction::NUM_ITEMS, ("Out of range.\n"));
7697 if (ndx <0 || ndx >= ScriptAction::NUM_ITEMS) ndx = 0;
7698 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH (!m_actionTemplates[ndx].getName().isEmpty(), ("Need to initialize action enum=%d.\n", ndx));
7699
7700 return &m_actionTemplates[ndx];
7701} // end getActionTemplate
7702
7703//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7705//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7706const ConditionTemplate * ScriptEngine::getConditionTemplate( Int ndx )
7707{
7708 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(ndx >= 0 && ndx < ScriptAction::NUM_ITEMS, ("Out of range.\n"));
7709 if (ndx <0 || ndx >= Condition::NUM_ITEMS) ndx = 0;
7710 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH (!m_conditionTemplates[ndx].getName().isEmpty(), ("Need to initialize Condition enum=%d.\n", ndx));
7711 return &m_conditionTemplates[ndx];
7712} // end getConditionTemplate

7714//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7716//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7717void ScriptEngine::createNamedCache( void )
7718{
7719 m_namedObjects.clear();
7720
7721 if( !TheGameLogic )
7722 {
7723 return;
7724 }
7725 Object* pObj = TheGameLogic->getFirstObject();
7726
7727 while (pObj) {
7728 if (!pObj->getName().isEmpty()) {
7729 NamedRequest req;
7730 req.first = pObj->getName();
7731 req.second = pObj;
7732 m_namedObjects.push_back(req);
7733 }
7734 pObj = pObj->getNextObject();
7735 }
7736}
7737
7738void ScriptEngine::appendSequentialScript(const SequentialScript *scriptToSequence)
7739{
7740 SequentialScript *newSequentialScript = newInstance( SequentialScript );
7741 (*newSequentialScript) = (*scriptToSequence);
7742
7743 // Must set this to NULL, as we don't want an infinite loop.
7744 newSequentialScript->m_nextScriptInSequence = NULL;
7745
7746 // reset the instruction pointer
7747 newSequentialScript->m_currentInstruction = -1;
7748
7749 VecSequentialScriptPtrIt it;
7750 Bool found = false;
7751 for (it = m_sequentialScripts.begin(); it != m_sequentialScripts.end(); ++it) {
7752 SequentialScript *seqScript = (*it);
7753 if (!seqScript) {
7754 continue;
7755 }
7756
7757 if ((scriptToSequence->m_objectID && scriptToSequence->m_objectID == seqScript->m_objectID) ||
7758 (scriptToSequence->m_teamToExecOn && scriptToSequence->m_teamToExecOn == seqScript->m_teamToExecOn)) {
7759 found = true;
7760 while (seqScript->m_nextScriptInSequence) {
7761 seqScript = seqScript->m_nextScriptInSequence;
7762 }
7763
7764 seqScript->m_nextScriptInSequence = newSequentialScript;
7765 break;
7766 }
7767 }
7768
7769 if (!found) {
7770 m_sequentialScripts.push_back(newSequentialScript);
7771 }
7772
7773 // do not delete either of these here.
7774}
7775
7776void ScriptEngine::removeSequentialScript(SequentialScript *scriptToRemove)
7777{
7778
7779}
7780
7781void ScriptEngine::removeAllSequentialScripts(Object *obj)
7782{
7783 if (!obj) {
7784 return;
7785 }
7786
7787 ObjectID id = obj->getID();
7788 VecSequentialScriptPtrIt it;
7789 for (it = m_sequentialScripts.begin(); it != m_sequentialScripts.end(); /* empty */) {
7790 SequentialScript *seqScript = (*it);
7791 if (!seqScript) {
7792 ++it;
7793 continue;
7794 }
7795 if (seqScript->m_objectID == id) {
7796 it = cleanupSequentialScript(it, TRUE);
7797 }
7798 else
7799 ++it;
7800 }
7801}
7802
7803void ScriptEngine::removeAllSequentialScripts(Team *team)
7804{
7805 // this function will remove all pending scripts for this team, so just call it.
7806 notifyOfTeamDestruction(team);
7807}

7811 m_frameObjectCountChanged = TheGameLogic->getFrame();

7813
7814void ScriptEngine::notifyOfTeamDestruction(Team *teamDestroyed)
7815{
7816 if (!teamDestroyed) {
7817 return;
7818 }
7819
7820 VecSequentialScriptPtrIt it;
7821 for (it = m_sequentialScripts.begin(); it != m_sequentialScripts.end(); /* empty */) {
7822 SequentialScript *seqScript = (*it);
7823 if (!seqScript) {
7824 continue;
7825 }
7826
7827 if (seqScript->m_teamToExecOn == teamDestroyed) {
7828 it = cleanupSequentialScript(it, TRUE);
7829 continue;
7830 }
7831 ++it;
7832 }
7833
7834 if (m_callingTeam == teamDestroyed)
7835 m_callingTeam = NULL;
7836 if (m_conditionTeam == teamDestroyed)
7837 m_conditionTeam = NULL;
7838}

7841{

7843 return;

7848 for (it = m_sequentialScripts.begin(); it != m_sequentialScripts.end(); ++it) {
7849 SequentialScript *seqScript = (*it);
7850 if (!seqScript) {
7851 continue;
7852 }
7853
7854 if (seqScript->m_objectID == id) {
7855 // this is it.
7856 seqScript->m_framesToWait = frameCount;
7857 return;
7858 }

7872 continue;

7882
7883
7884void ScriptEngine::evaluateAndProgressAllSequentialScripts( void )
7885{
7886 VecSequentialScriptPtrIt it, lastIt;
7887 lastIt = m_sequentialScripts.end();
7888
7889 Int spinCount = 0;
7890 for (it = m_sequentialScripts.begin(); it != m_sequentialScripts.end(); /* empty */) {
7891 if (it == lastIt) {
7892 ++spinCount;
7893 } else {
7894 spinCount = 0;
7895 }
7896
7897 if (spinCount > MAX_SPIN_COUNT) {
7898 SequentialScript *seqScript = (*it);
7899 if (seqScript) {
7900 DEBUG_LOG(("Sequential script %s appears to be in an infinite loop.\n",
7901 seqScript->m_scriptToExecuteSequentially->getName().str()));
7902 }
7903 ++it;
7904 continue;
7905 }
7906
7907 lastIt = it;
7908
7909 Bool itAdvanced = false;
7910
7911 SequentialScript *seqScript = (*it);
7912 if (seqScript == NULL) {
7913 it = cleanupSequentialScript(it, false);
7914 continue;
7915 }
7916
7917 Team *team = seqScript->m_teamToExecOn;
7918 Object *obj = TheGameLogic->findObjectByID(seqScript->m_objectID);
7919 if (!(obj || team)) {
7920 it = cleanupSequentialScript(it, false);
7921 itAdvanced = true;
7922 continue;
7923 }
7924 m_currentPlayer = NULL;
7925 if (obj) {
7926 m_currentPlayer = obj->getControllingPlayer();
7927 } else if (team) {
7928 m_currentPlayer = team->getControllingPlayer();
7929 }
7930 if (m_currentPlayer && !m_currentPlayer->isSkirmishAIPlayer()) {
7931 m_currentPlayer = NULL;
7932 }
7933
7934 AIUpdateInterface *ai = obj ? obj->getAIUpdateInterface() : NULL;
7935 AIGroup *aigroup = (team ? TheAI->createGroup() : NULL);
7936 if (aigroup) {
7937 team->getTeamAsAIGroup(aigroup);
7938 }
7939
7940 if( ai || aigroup ) {
7941 if (((ai && (ai->isIdle()) || (aigroup && aigroup->isIdle())) &&
7942 seqScript->m_framesToWait < 1) || (seqScript->m_framesToWait == 0)) {
7943
7944 // We want to supress messages if we're repeatedly waiting for an event to occur, cause
7945 // it KILLS our debug framerate.
7946 Bool displayMessage = TRUE;
7947
7948 // Time to progress to the next task.
7949 if (seqScript->m_dontAdvanceInstruction) {
7950 seqScript->m_dontAdvanceInstruction = FALSE;
7951 displayMessage = FALSE;
7952 } else {
7953 ++seqScript->m_currentInstruction;
7954 }
7955
7956 AsciiString msg = "Advancing SeqScript '";
7957 msg.concat(seqScript->m_scriptToExecuteSequentially->getName());
7958 msg.concat("' on ");
7959 AsciiString name;
7960 if (team) name = team->getName();
7961 if (obj) name = obj->getName();
7962 msg.concat(name);
7963 msg.concat(" -- ");
7964
7965 int instruction = seqScript->m_currentInstruction;
7966 ScriptAction *action = seqScript->m_scriptToExecuteSequentially->getAction();
7967 while (action && instruction) {
7968 --instruction;
7969 action = action->getNext();
7970 }
7971
7972 if (action) {
7973 m_conditionTeam = team;
7974 m_conditionObject = obj;
7975 seqScript->m_framesToWait = -1;
7976
7977 // Save off the next action
7978 ScriptAction *nextAction = action->getNext();
7979 action->setNextAction(NULL);
7980 if (action->getActionType() == ScriptAction::SKIRMISH_WAIT_FOR_COMMANDBUTTON_AVAILABLE_ALL) {
7981 if (!TheScriptConditions->evaluateSkirmishCommandButtonIsReady(NULL, action->getParameter(1), action->getParameter(2), true)) {
7982 seqScript->m_dontAdvanceInstruction = TRUE;
7983 }
7984 } else if (action->getActionType() == ScriptAction::SKIRMISH_WAIT_FOR_COMMANDBUTTON_AVAILABLE_PARTIAL) {
7985 if (!TheScriptConditions->evaluateSkirmishCommandButtonIsReady(NULL, action->getParameter(1), action->getParameter(2), false)) {
7986 seqScript->m_dontAdvanceInstruction = TRUE;
7987 }
7988 } else if (action->getActionType() == ScriptAction::TEAM_WAIT_FOR_NOT_CONTAINED_ALL) {
7989 if (TheScriptConditions->evaluateTeamIsContained(action->getParameter(0), true)) {
7990 seqScript->m_dontAdvanceInstruction = TRUE;
7991 }
7992 } else if (action->getActionType() == ScriptAction::TEAM_WAIT_FOR_NOT_CONTAINED_PARTIAL) {
7993 if (TheScriptConditions->evaluateTeamIsContained(action->getParameter(0), false)) {
7994 seqScript->m_dontAdvanceInstruction = TRUE;
7995 }
7996 } else {
7997 executeActions(action);
7998 }
7999
8000 if (displayMessage) {
8001 msg.concat(action->getUiText());
8002 AppendDebugMessage(msg, false);
8003 } else {
8004 msg.clear();
8005 }
8006
8007 action->setNextAction(nextAction);
8008
8009 // Check to see if executing our action told us to wait. If so, skip to the next Sequential script
8010 if (seqScript->m_dontAdvanceInstruction) {
8011 ++it;
8012 itAdvanced = true;
8013 continue;
8014 }
8015
8016 if (ai && ai->isIdle()) {
8017 // pretend like we've already advanced to allow multiple checks on this object this frame.
8018 itAdvanced = true;
8019 } else if (team) {
8020 // attempt to rebuild the aigroup, as it probably expired during the action execution
8021 aigroup = (team ? TheAI->createGroup() : NULL);
8022 team->getTeamAsAIGroup(aigroup);
8023 }
8024
8025 if (aigroup && aigroup->isIdle()) {
8026 // pretend like we've already advanced to allow multiple checks on this object this frame.
8027 itAdvanced = true;
8028 }
8029
8030 if (itAdvanced) { // check to make sure they aren't dead.
8031 if (obj && obj->isEffectivelyDead()) {
8032 it = cleanupSequentialScript(it, true);
8033 continue;
8034 }
8035
8036 if (aigroup && aigroup->isGroupAiDead()) {
8037 it = cleanupSequentialScript(it, true);
8038 continue;
8039 }
8040 }
8041 } else {
8042 if (seqScript->m_timesToLoop != 0) {
8043 if (seqScript->m_timesToLoop != -1) {
8044 --seqScript->m_timesToLoop;
8045 }
8046
8047 seqScript->m_framesToWait = -1;
8048 appendSequentialScript(seqScript);
8049 }
8050
8051 it = cleanupSequentialScript(it, false);
8052 itAdvanced = true;
8053 }
8054 } else if (seqScript->m_framesToWait > 0) {
8055 --seqScript->m_framesToWait;
8056 }
8057 }
8058
8059 if (!itAdvanced) {
8060 ++it;
8061 }
8062 }
8063 m_currentPlayer = NULL;
8064}
8065
8066ScriptEngine::VecSequentialScriptPtrIt ScriptEngine::cleanupSequentialScript(VecSequentialScriptPtrIt it, Bool cleanDanglers)
8067{
8068 SequentialScript *seqScript;
8069 seqScript = (*it);
8070 if (!seqScript) {
8071 return it;
8072 }
8073
8074 SequentialScript *scriptToDelete = seqScript;
8075 if (cleanDanglers) {
8076 while (seqScript) {
8077 scriptToDelete = seqScript;
8078 seqScript = seqScript->m_nextScriptInSequence;
8079 scriptToDelete->deleteInstance();
8080 scriptToDelete = NULL;
8081 }
8082 (*it) = NULL;
8083 } else {
8084 // we want to make sure to not delete any dangling scripts.
8085 (*it) = scriptToDelete->m_nextScriptInSequence;
8086 scriptToDelete->deleteInstance();
8087 scriptToDelete = NULL;
8088 }
8089
8090
8091 if ((*it) == NULL) {
8092 return m_sequentialScripts.erase(it);
8093 }
8094
8095 return it;
8096}

8127SequentialScript::SequentialScript() : m_teamToExecOn(NULL),
8128 m_objectID(INVALID_ID),
8129 m_scriptToExecuteSequentially(NULL),
8130 m_currentInstruction(START_INSTRUCTION),
8131 m_timesToLoop(0),
8132 m_framesToWait(-1),
8133 m_dontAdvanceInstruction(FALSE),
8134 m_nextScriptInSequence(NULL)

8146// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8150// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8151void SequentialScript::xfer( Xfer *xfer )
8152{
8153
8154 // version
8155 XferVersion currentVersion = 1;
8156 XferVersion version = currentVersion;
8157 xfer->xferVersion( &version, currentVersion );
8158
8159 // team
8160 TeamID teamID = m_teamToExecOn ? m_teamToExecOn->getID() : TEAM_ID_INVALID;
8161 xfer->xferUser( &teamID, sizeof( TeamID ) );
8162 if( xfer->getXferMode() == XFER_LOAD )
8163 {
8164
8165 // tie up pointer
8166 m_teamToExecOn = TheTeamFactory->findTeamByID( teamID );
8167
8168 // sanity
8169 if( teamID != TEAM_ID_INVALID && m_teamToExecOn == NULL )
8170 {
8171
8172 DEBUG_CRASH(( "SequentialScript::xfer - Unable to find team by ID (#%d) for m_teamToExecOn\n",
8173 teamID ));
8174 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
8175
8176 } // end if
8177
8178 } // end if
8179
8180 // object id
8181 xfer->xferObjectID( &m_objectID );
8182
8183 // saving
8184 AsciiString scriptName;
8185 if( xfer->getXferMode() == XFER_SAVE )
8186 {
8187
8188 // write script name
8189 scriptName = m_scriptToExecuteSequentially->getName();
8190 xfer->xferAsciiString( &scriptName );
8191
8192 } // end if, save
8193 else
8194 {
8195
8196 // read script name
8197 xfer->xferAsciiString( &scriptName );
8198
8199 // script pointer
8200 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH( m_scriptToExecuteSequentially == NULL, ("SequentialScript::xfer - m_scripttoExecuteSequentially\n") );
8201
8202 // find script
8203 m_scriptToExecuteSequentially = const_cast<Script*>(TheScriptEngine->findScriptByName(scriptName));
8204
8205 // sanity
8206 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH( m_scriptToExecuteSequentially != NULL,
8207 ("SequentialScript::xfer - m_scriptToExecuteSequentially is NULL but should not be\n") );
8208
8209 } // end else, load
8210
8211 // current instruction
8212 xfer->xferInt( &m_currentInstruction );
8213
8214 // times to loop
8215 xfer->xferInt( &m_timesToLoop );
8216
8217 // frames to wait
8218 xfer->xferInt( &m_framesToWait );
8219
8220 // dont advance instruction
8221 xfer->xferBool( &m_dontAdvanceInstruction );
8222
8223} // end xfer

8276//----Particle Editor Stuff------------------------------------------------------------------------
8277//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8279//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8280void ScriptEngine::particleEditorUpdate( void )
8281{
8282 if (!st_ParticleDLL) {
8283 return;
8284 }
8285
8286 _updateCurrentParticleCount();
8287
8288 Bool busyWait = false;
8289 do {
8290 if (m_firstUpdate) {
8291 _appendAllParticleSystems();
8292 _appendAllThingTemplates();
8293 } else {
8294 switch (_getEditorBehavior())
8295 {
8296 case 0x00:
8297 {
8298 busyWait = false;
8299 return;
8300 }
8301
8302 case 0x01:
8303 case 0x02:
8304 {
8305 _updateAndSetCurrentSystem();
8306 busyWait = false;
8307 break;
8308 }
8309
8310 case 0x03:
8311 {
8312 AsciiString particleSystemName = _getParticleSystemName();
8313 _addUpdatedParticleSystem(particleSystemName);
8314 ParticleSystemTemplate *pTemp = const_cast<ParticleSystemTemplate*>(TheParticleSystemManager->findTemplate(particleSystemName));
8315 if (pTemp) {
8316 // make sure that this system is fully up to date.
8317 _updateAsciiStringParmsToSystem(pTemp);
8318 }
8319 _writeOutINI();
8320 busyWait = false;
8321 break;
8322 }
8323
8324 case 0x04:
8325 {
8326 AsciiString particleSystemName = _getParticleSystemName();
8327 _reloadParticleSystemFromINI(particleSystemName);
8328 busyWait = false;
8329 return;
8330 }
8331
8332 case 0x05:
8333 {
8334 int newCap = _getNewCurrentParticleCap();
8335 if (newCap >= 0) {
8336 TheWritableGlobalData->m_maxParticleCount = newCap;
8337 }
8338 busyWait = false;
8339 }
8340
8341 case 0x06:
8342 {
8343 _reloadTextures();
8344 busyWait = false;
8345 break;
8346 }
8347
8348 // destroy all particle systems
8349 case 0x07:
8350 {
8351
8352 TheParticleSystemManager->reset();
8353
8354/*
8355 //iterate through particle system list and remove each particle system
8356 ParticleSystemManager::ParticleSystemList particleSysList;
8357 ParticleSystemManager::ParticleSystemListIt it;
8358 while (true)
8359 {
8360 // reassign values into variables
8361 particleSysList = TheParticleSystemManager->getAllParticleSystems();
8362 it = particleSysList.begin();
8363 if (it == particleSysList.end())
8364 break;
8365
8366 // check to make sure the particle system is valid
8367 ParticleSystem *sys = (*it);
8368 if (!sys)
8369 continue;
8370
8371 //before removing the system, make sure to remove all of its particles individually
8372 while (sys->getParticleCount() > 0) {
8373 TheParticleSystemManager->removeParticle(sys->getFirstParticle());
8374 sys->removeParticle(sys->getFirstParticle());
8375 }
8376
8377 TheParticleSystemManager->removeParticleSystem(sys);
8378 ++it;
8379 }
8380*/
8381
8382 //Int particleNum = TheParticleSystemManager->getParticleCount();
8383 _updateCurrentParticleCount(); // probably don't need this...
8384 }
8385
8386 case 0xFE:
8387 {
8388 busyWait = true;
8389 break;
8390 }
8391
8392 case 0xFF:
8393 {
8394 busyWait = false;
8395 break;
8396 }
8397 }
8398 }
8399 } while (busyWait);
8400}

8426//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8428//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8429Bool ScriptEngine::isTimeFrozenDebug(void)
8430{
8431 typedef Bool (*funcptr)(void);
8432
8433 if (st_DebugDLL) {
8434 if (st_LastCurrentFrame != st_CurrentFrame) {
8435 st_LastCurrentFrame = st_CurrentFrame;
8436
8437 FARPROC proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "CanAppContinue");
8438 if (proc) {
8439 st_CanAppCont = ((funcptr)proc)();
8440
8441 if (st_CanAppCont) {
8442 }
8443 }
8444 }
8445 return !st_CanAppCont;
8446 }
8447 return false;
8448}

8450//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8452//-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8453Bool ScriptEngine::isTimeFast(void)
8454{
8455 typedef Bool (*funcptr)(void);
8456
8457 if (st_DebugDLL) {
8458 FARPROC proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "CanAppContinue");
8459 proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "RunAppFast");
8460 if (proc && ((funcptr)proc)()) {
8461 st_AppIsFast = true;
8462 } else {
8463 if (st_AppIsFast) {
8464 st_AppIsFast = false;
8465 }
8466 }
8467 if (st_AppIsFast) {
8468 if ((TheGameLogic->getFrame()%10) == 0) {
8469 return false;
8470 }
8471 return true;
8472 } else {
8473 return false;
8474 }
8475 }
8476 return false;
8477}

8479void ScriptEngine::forceUnfreezeTime(void)
8480{

8482
8483 if (st_DebugDLL) {
8484 FARPROC proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "ForceAppContinue");
8485 if (proc) {
8486 ((funcptr)proc)();
8487 }
8488 }
8489}
8490
8491void ScriptEngine::AppendDebugMessage(const AsciiString& strToAdd, Bool forcePause)
8492{
8493#ifdef INTENSE_DEBUG
8494 DEBUG_LOG(("-SCRIPT- %d %s\n", TheGameLogic->getFrame(), strToAdd.str()));
8495#endif
8496 typedef void (*funcptr)(const char*);
8497 if (!st_DebugDLL) {
8498 return;
8499 }
8500
8501 FARPROC proc;
8502 if (forcePause) {
8503 proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "AppendMessageAndPause");
8504 } else {
8505 proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "AppendMessage");
8506 }
8507
8508 if (!proc) {
8509 return;
8510 }
8511 AsciiString msg;
8512 msg.format("%d ", TheGameLogic->getFrame());
8513 msg.concat(strToAdd);
8514 ((funcptr)proc)(msg.str());
8515}

8518{
8519 _adjustVariable(variableName, value, (forcePause != 0));
8520}

8530// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8533// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8534static void xferListAsciiString( Xfer *xfer, ListAsciiString *list )
8535{
8536
8537 // sanity
8538 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH( list != NULL, ("xferListAsciiString - Invalid parameters\n") );
8539
8540 // version
8541 XferVersion currentVersion = 1;
8542 XferVersion version = currentVersion;
8543 xfer->xferVersion( &version, currentVersion );
8544
8545 // size of list
8546 UnsignedShort count = list->size();
8547 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &count );
8548
8549 // list data
8550 AsciiString string;
8551 if( xfer->getXferMode() == XFER_SAVE )
8552 {
8553
8554 // write each string
8555 ListAsciiStringIt it;
8556 for( it = list->begin(); it != list->end(); ++it )
8557 {
8558
8559 string = *it;
8560 xfer->xferAsciiString( &string );
8561
8562 } // end for, it
8563
8564 } // end if, save
8565 else
8566 {
8567
8568 // this list should be empty upon loading
8569 if( list->empty() == FALSE )
8570 {
8571
8572 DEBUG_CRASH(( "xferListAsciiString - list should be empty upon loading but is not\n" ));
8573 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
8574
8575 } // end if
8576
8577 // read each string
8578 for( UnsignedShort i = 0; i < count; ++i )
8579 {
8580
8581 // read string
8582 xfer->xferAsciiString( &string );
8583
8584 // put on list
8585 list->push_back( string );
8586
8587 } // end for, i
8588
8589 } // end else, load
8590
8591} // end xferListAsciiString

8607

8621 {
8622

8625 xfer->xferAsciiString( &string );
8626
8627 // unsigned int data
8628 unsignedIntData = it->second;
8629 xfer->xferUnsignedInt( &unsignedIntData );
8630

8632
8633 } // end if, save
8634 else
8635 {
8636 PairAsciiStringUINT newPair;
8637
8638 // this list should be empty upon loading

8641

8644

8648 for( UnsignedShort i = 0; i < count; ++i )
8649 {
8650
8651 // read string
8652 xfer->xferAsciiString( &string );
8653
8654 // read unsigned int data

8656
8657 // put on list

8661
8662 } // end for, i
8663
8664 } // end else, load

8826// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8835// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8836void ScriptEngine::xfer( Xfer *xfer )
8837{
8838 Int i;
8839
8840 // version
8841 const XferVersion currentVersion = 5;
8842 XferVersion version = currentVersion;
8843 xfer->xferVersion( &version, currentVersion );
8844
8845 // sequential script count and data
8846 UnsignedShort sequentialScriptCount = m_sequentialScripts.size();
8847 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &sequentialScriptCount );
8848 SequentialScript *sequentialScript;
8849 if( xfer->getXferMode() == XFER_SAVE )
8850 {
8851
8852 // save each element
8853 VecSequentialScriptPtrIt it;
8854 for( it = m_sequentialScripts.begin(); it != m_sequentialScripts.end(); ++it )
8855 {
8856
8857 // get data
8858 sequentialScript = *it;
8859
8860 // xfer data
8861 xfer->xferSnapshot( sequentialScript );
8862
8863 } // end for, it
8864
8865 } // end if, save
8866 else
8867 {
8868
8869 // this list should be empty on loading
8870 if( m_sequentialScripts.size() != 0 )
8871 {
8872
8873 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - m_sequentialScripts should be empty but is not\n" ));
8874 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
8875
8876 } // end if
8877
8878 // read each entry
8879 for( UnsignedShort i = 0; i < sequentialScriptCount; ++i )
8880 {
8881
8882 // allocate new sequential script and put on our list
8883 sequentialScript = newInstance( SequentialScript );
8884
8885 // tie to our list
8886 m_sequentialScripts.push_back( sequentialScript );
8887
8888 // xfer data
8889 xfer->xferSnapshot( sequentialScript );
8890
8891 } // end for i
8892
8893 } // end else, load
8894
8895 // counters
8896 UnsignedShort countersSize = m_numCounters;
8897 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &countersSize );
8898 if( countersSize > MAX_COUNTERS )
8899 {
8900
8901 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - MAX_COUNTERS has changed size, need to version this\n" ));
8902 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
8903
8904 } // end if
8905 for( i = 0; i < countersSize; ++i )
8906 {
8907
8908 // value
8909 xfer->xferInt( &m_counters[ i ].value );
8910
8911 // name
8912 xfer->xferAsciiString( &m_counters[ i ].name );
8913
8914 // countdown timer
8915 xfer->xferBool( &m_counters[ i ].isCountdownTimer );
8916
8917 } // end for, i
8918
8919 // num counters
8920 xfer->xferInt( &m_numCounters );
8921
8922 // flags
8923 UnsignedShort flagsSize = m_numFlags;
8924 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &flagsSize );
8925 if( flagsSize > MAX_FLAGS )
8926 {
8927
8928 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - MAX_FLAGS has changed size, need to version this\n" ));
8929 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
8930
8931 } // end if
8932 for( i = 0; i < flagsSize; ++i )
8933 {
8934
8935 // value
8936 xfer->xferBool( &m_flags[ i ].value );
8937
8938 // name
8939 xfer->xferAsciiString( &m_flags[ i ].name );
8940
8941 } // end for i
8942
8943 // num flags
8944 xfer->xferInt( &m_numFlags );
8945
8946 // attack priority info
8947 UnsignedShort attackPriorityInfoSize = m_numAttackInfo;
8948 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &attackPriorityInfoSize );
8949 if( attackPriorityInfoSize > MAX_ATTACK_PRIORITIES )
8950 {
8951
8952 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - MAX_ATTACK_PRIORITIES size has changed, need to version this\n" ));
8953 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
8954
8955 } // end if
8956 for( i = 0; i < attackPriorityInfoSize; ++i )
8957 {
8958
8959 // xfer each data
8960 xfer->xferSnapshot( &m_attackPriorityInfo[ i ] );
8961
8962 } // end for i
8963
8964 // num attack info
8965 xfer->xferInt( &m_numAttackInfo );
8966
8967 // end game timers
8968 xfer->xferInt( &m_endGameTimer );
8969 xfer->xferInt( &m_closeWindowTimer );
8970
8971 // named objects
8972 UnsignedShort namedObjectsCount = m_namedObjects.size();
8973 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &namedObjectsCount );
8974 AsciiString namedObjectName;
8975 Object *obj;
8976 ObjectID objectID;
8977 if( xfer->getXferMode() == XFER_SAVE )
8978 {
8979
8980 // iterate elemnts
8981 VecNamedRequestsIt it;
8982 for( it = m_namedObjects.begin(); it != m_namedObjects.end(); ++it )
8983 {
8984
8985 // write name
8986 namedObjectName = it->first;
8987 xfer->xferAsciiString( &namedObjectName );
8988
8989 // write object id (note that object may be NULL)
8990 obj = it->second;
8991 objectID = obj ? obj->getID() : INVALID_ID;
8992 xfer->xferObjectID( &objectID );
8993
8994 } // end for i
8995
8996 } // end if, save
8997 else
8998 {
8999 NamedRequest req;
9000
9001 //
9002 // list should be empty, it is legal for it to not be empty at this point
9003 // according to John M., so we're clearing it now
9004 //
9005 m_namedObjects.clear();
9006
9007 // read each element
9008 for( UnsignedShort i = 0; i < namedObjectsCount; ++i )
9009 {
9010
9011 // read name
9012 xfer->xferAsciiString( &namedObjectName );
9013
9014 // read object id and turn into object pointer
9015 xfer->xferObjectID( &objectID );
9016 obj = TheGameLogic->findObjectByID( objectID );
9017 if( obj == NULL && objectID != INVALID_ID )
9018 {
9019
9020 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - Unable to find object by ID for m_namedObjects\n" ));
9021 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
9022
9023 } // end if
9024
9025 // assign
9026 req.first = namedObjectName;
9027 req.second = obj;
9028 m_namedObjects.push_back( req );
9029
9030 } // end for, i
9031
9032 } // end else, load
9033
9034 // first update
9035 xfer->xferBool( &m_firstUpdate );
9036
9037 // trade (this needs a better descriptive name (CBD)
9038 xfer->xferUser( &m_fade, sizeof( TFade ) );
9039
9040 // min fade
9041 xfer->xferReal( &m_minFade );
9042
9043 // max fade
9044 xfer->xferReal( &m_maxFade );
9045
9046 // curr fade value
9047 xfer->xferReal( &m_curFadeValue );
9048
9049 // current fade frame
9050 xfer->xferInt( &m_curFadeFrame );
9051
9052 // fade frames increase
9053 xfer->xferInt( &m_fadeFramesIncrease );
9054
9055 // fade frames hold
9056 xfer->xferInt( &m_fadeFramesHold );
9057
9058 // fade frames decrease
9059 xfer->xferInt( &m_fadeFramesDecrease );
9060
9061 // complete video
9062 xferListAsciiString( xfer, &m_completedVideo );
9063
9064 // testing speech
9065 xferListAsciiStringUINT( xfer, &m_testingSpeech );
9066
9067 // testing audio
9068 xferListAsciiStringUINT( xfer, &m_testingAudio );
9069
9070 // ui interactions
9071 xferListAsciiString( xfer, &m_uiInteractions );
9072
9073 // triggered special powers
9074 UnsignedShort triggeredSpecialPowersSize = MAX_PLAYER_COUNT;
9075 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &triggeredSpecialPowersSize );
9076 if( triggeredSpecialPowersSize != MAX_PLAYER_COUNT )
9077 {
9078
9079 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - MAX_PLAYER_COUNT has changed, m_triggeredSpecialPowers size is now different and we must version this\n" ));
9080 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
9081
9082 } // end if
9083 for( i = 0; i < triggeredSpecialPowersSize; ++i )
9084 xferListAsciiStringObjectID( xfer, &m_triggeredSpecialPowers[ i ] );
9085
9086 // midway special powers
9087 UnsignedShort midwaySpecialPowersSize = MAX_PLAYER_COUNT;
9088 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &midwaySpecialPowersSize );
9089 if( midwaySpecialPowersSize != MAX_PLAYER_COUNT )
9090 {
9091
9092 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - MAX_PLAYER_COUNT has changed, m_midwaySpecialPowers size is now different and we must version this\n" ));
9093 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
9094
9095 } // end if
9096 for( i = 0; i < midwaySpecialPowersSize; ++i )
9097 xferListAsciiStringObjectID( xfer, &m_midwaySpecialPowers[ i ] );
9098
9099 // finished special powers
9100 UnsignedShort finishedSpecialPowersSize = MAX_PLAYER_COUNT;
9101 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &finishedSpecialPowersSize );
9102 if( finishedSpecialPowersSize != MAX_PLAYER_COUNT )
9103 {
9104
9105 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - MAX_PLAYER_COUNT has changed, m_finishedSpecialPowers size is now different and we must version this\n" ));
9106 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
9107
9108 } // end if
9109 for( i = 0; i < finishedSpecialPowersSize; ++i )
9110 xferListAsciiStringObjectID( xfer, &m_finishedSpecialPowers[ i ] );
9111
9112 // completed upgrades
9113 UnsignedShort completedUpgradesSize = MAX_PLAYER_COUNT;
9114 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &completedUpgradesSize );
9115 if( completedUpgradesSize != MAX_PLAYER_COUNT )
9116 {
9117
9118 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - MAX_PLAYER_COUNT has changed, m_completedUpgrades size is now different and we must version this\n" ));
9119 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
9120
9121 } // end if
9122 for( i = 0; i < completedUpgradesSize; ++i )
9123 xferListAsciiStringObjectID( xfer, &m_completedUpgrades[ i ] );
9124
9125 // acquired sciences
9126 UnsignedShort acquiredSciencesSize = MAX_PLAYER_COUNT;
9127 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &acquiredSciencesSize );
9128 if( acquiredSciencesSize != MAX_PLAYER_COUNT )
9129 {
9130
9131 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - MAX_PLAYER_COUNT has changed, m_acquiredSciences size is now different and we must version this\n" ));
9132 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
9133
9134 } // end if
9135 for( i = 0; i < acquiredSciencesSize; ++i )
9136 xfer->xferScienceVec( &m_acquiredSciences[ i ] );
9137
9138 // topple directions
9139 xferListAsciiStringCoord3D( xfer, &m_toppleDirections );
9140
9141 // breeze info
9142 xfer->xferReal( &m_breezeInfo.m_direction );
9143 xfer->xferReal( &m_breezeInfo.m_directionVec.x );
9144 xfer->xferReal( &m_breezeInfo.m_directionVec.y );
9145 xfer->xferReal( &m_breezeInfo.m_intensity );
9146 xfer->xferReal( &m_breezeInfo.m_lean );
9147 xfer->xferReal( &m_breezeInfo.m_randomness );
9148 xfer->xferShort( &m_breezeInfo.m_breezePeriod );
9149 xfer->xferShort( &m_breezeInfo.m_breezeVersion );
9150
9151 // game difficulty
9152 xfer->xferUser( &m_gameDifficulty, sizeof( GameDifficulty ) );
9153
9154 // freeze by script
9155 xfer->xferBool( &m_freezeByScript );
9156
9157 // version 2
9158 if( version >= 2 )
9159 {
9160
9161 // number of entries in named reveals
9162 UnsignedShort namedRevealCount = m_namedReveals.size();
9163 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &namedRevealCount );
9164
9165 // named reveal data
9166 if( xfer->getXferMode() == XFER_SAVE )
9167 {
9168
9169 // iterate vector
9170 VecNamedRevealIt it;
9171 for( it = m_namedReveals.begin(); it != m_namedReveals.end(); ++it )
9172 {
9173
9174 // name
9175 xfer->xferAsciiString( &it->m_revealName );
9176
9177 // waypoint name
9178 xfer->xferAsciiString( &it->m_waypointName );
9179
9180 // radius
9181 xfer->xferReal( &it->m_radiusToReveal );
9182
9183 // player name
9184 xfer->xferAsciiString( &it->m_playerName );
9185
9186 } // end for, it
9187
9188 } // end if, save
9189 else
9190 {
9191
9192 // the vector should be emtpy now
9193 if( m_namedReveals.empty() == FALSE )
9194 {
9195
9196 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - m_namedReveals should be empty but is not!\n" ));
9197 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
9198
9199 } // end if
9200
9201 // read all entries
9202 NamedReveal reveal;
9203 for( UnsignedShort i = 0; i < namedRevealCount; ++i )
9204 {
9205
9206 // read name
9207 xfer->xferAsciiString( &reveal.m_revealName );
9208
9209 // read waypoint name
9210 xfer->xferAsciiString( &reveal.m_waypointName );
9211
9212 // read radius
9213 xfer->xferReal( &reveal.m_radiusToReveal );
9214
9215 // read player name
9216 xfer->xferAsciiString( &reveal.m_playerName );
9217
9218 // put on list
9219 m_namedReveals.push_back( reveal );
9220
9221 } // end for, i
9222
9223 } // end else, load
9224
9225 // all object type lists size
9226 UnsignedShort allObjectTypesCount = m_allObjectTypeLists.size();
9227 xfer->xferUnsignedShort( &allObjectTypesCount );
9228
9229 // all object type lists data
9230 if( xfer->getXferMode() == XFER_SAVE )
9231 {
9232
9233 // iterate list
9234 AllObjectTypesIt it;
9235 ObjectTypes *objectTypes;
9236 for( it = m_allObjectTypeLists.begin(); it != m_allObjectTypeLists.end(); ++it )
9237 {
9238
9239 // get object types from iterator
9240 objectTypes = *it;
9241
9242 // save object types
9243 xfer->xferSnapshot( objectTypes );
9244
9245 } // end for, it
9246
9247 } // end if, save
9248 else
9249 {
9250
9251 // sanity, the list should be empty now
9252 if( m_allObjectTypeLists.empty() == FALSE )
9253 {
9254
9255 DEBUG_CRASH(( "ScriptEngine::xfer - m_allObjectTypeLists should be empty but is not!\n" ));
9256 throw SC_INVALID_DATA;
9257
9258 } // end if
9259
9260 // read all data
9261 ObjectTypes *objectTypes;
9262 for( UnsignedShort i = 0; i < allObjectTypesCount; ++i )
9263 {
9264
9265 // allocate a new object types
9266 objectTypes = newInstance( ObjectTypes );
9267
9268 // xfer object types data
9269 xfer->xferSnapshot( objectTypes );
9270
9271 // put on list
9272 m_allObjectTypeLists.push_back( objectTypes );
9273
9274 } // end for, i
9275
9276 } // end else, load
9277
9278 } // end if, version 2
9279
9280 if (version >= 3) {
9281 xfer->xferBool(&m_objectsShouldReceiveDifficultyBonus);
9282 } else {
9283 m_objectsShouldReceiveDifficultyBonus = TRUE;
9284 }
9285
9286 if (version >= 4)
9287 {
9288 xfer->xferAsciiString(&m_currentTrackName);
9289 }
9290
9291 if (version >= 5)
9292 {
9293 xfer->xferBool(&m_ChooseVictimAlwaysUsesNormal);
9294 }
9295 else
9296 {
9297 m_ChooseVictimAlwaysUsesNormal = false;
9298 }
9299
9300 if( xfer->getXferMode() == XFER_LOAD ) {
9301 // We are doing a load. If there is no fade active, do a black fade in to start.
9302 if (m_fade == FADE_NONE) {
9303 m_fade = FADE_MULTIPLY; //default to a fade in from black.
9304 m_curFadeFrame = 0;
9305 m_minFade = 1.0f;
9306 m_maxFade = 0.0f;
9307 m_fadeFramesIncrease = 0;
9308 m_fadeFramesHold = 0;
9309 m_fadeFramesDecrease = FRAMES_TO_FADE_IN_AT_START;
9310 m_curFadeValue = 0.0f;
9311 }
9312 }
9313} // end xfer

9317// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9318void ScriptEngine::loadPostProcess( void )
9319{
9320
9321 // Now that we've loaded everything, go through and set them all back in sync with what we
9322 // currently think they should be.
9323 TheScriptActions->doEnableOrDisableObjectDifficultyBonuses(m_objectsShouldReceiveDifficultyBonus);
9324
9325 if (m_currentTrackName.isNotEmpty())
9326 {
9327 AudioEventRTS event(m_currentTrackName);
9328 event.setPlayerIndex(ThePlayerList->getLocalPlayer()->getPlayerIndex());
9329 TheAudio->addAudioEvent(&event);
9330 }
9331
9332} // end loadPostProcess

9356void _appendMessage(const AsciiString& str, Bool isTrueMessage, Bool shouldPause)
9357{
9358 typedef void (*funcptr)(const char*);
9359
9360 AsciiString msg;
9361 msg.format("%d ", TheGameLogic->getFrame());
9362 if (isTrueMessage) {
9363 msg.concat("Run script - ");
9364 } else {
9365 msg.concat("Run script false -");
9366 }
9367 msg.concat(str);
9368
9369#ifdef INTENSE_DEBUG
9370 DEBUG_LOG(("-SCRIPT- %s\n", msg.str()));
9371#endif
9372 if (!st_DebugDLL) {
9373 return;
9374 }
9375
9376 FARPROC proc;
9377 if (shouldPause) {
9378 proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "AppendMessageAndPause");
9379 } else {
9380 proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "AppendMessage");
9381 }
9382 if (!proc) {
9383 return;
9384 }
9385
9386 ((funcptr)proc)(msg.str());
9387}

9398 proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "AdjustVariableAndPause");
9399 } else {
9400 proc = GetProcAddress(st_DebugDLL, "AdjustVariable");
9401 }
9402
9403 if (!proc) {
9404 return;
9405 }
9406
9407 char buff[12]; // for sprintf
9408 sprintf(buff, "%d", value);
9409
9410 ((funcptr)proc)(str.str(), buff);
9411}

9432void _appendAllParticleSystems( void )
9433{
9434 typedef void (*funcptr)(const char*);
9435 if (!st_ParticleDLL) {
9436 return;
9437 }
9438 FARPROC proc;
9439
9440 proc = GetProcAddress(st_ParticleDLL, "RemoveAllParticleSystems");
9441 if (proc) {
9442 proc();
9443 } else {
9444 return;
9445 }
9446
9447 proc = GetProcAddress(st_ParticleDLL, "AppendParticleSystem");
9448 if (!proc) {
9449 return;
9450 }
9451
9452 // Copy just the names for the list of particle system templates
9453 ParticleSystemManager::TemplateMap::iterator begin(TheParticleSystemManager->beginParticleSystemTemplate());
9454 ParticleSystemManager::TemplateMap::iterator end(TheParticleSystemManager->endParticleSystemTemplate());
9455 for (; begin != end; ++begin) {
9456 ((funcptr)proc)((*begin).first.str());
9457 }
9458}

9491{

9493 typedef void (*funcptr2)(ParticleSystemTemplate*);

9495 return;

9499 return;

9504 if (!proc) {
9505 return;

9515 if (!pTemplate) {
9516 return;

9519 ((funcptr)proc)(pTemplate->getName().str());
9520 ((funcptr2)proc2)(pTemplate);

9561void _updateAsciiStringParmsToSystem( ParticleSystemTemplate *particleTemplate )
9562{
9563 typedef void (*funcptr)(int, char*, ParticleSystemTemplate **);
9564
9565 if (!st_ParticleDLL || !particleTemplate) {
9566 return;
9567 }
9568
9569 FARPROC proc;
9570 proc = GetProcAddress(st_ParticleDLL, "GetSelectedParticleAsciiStringParm");
9571
9572 if (!proc) {
9573 return;
9574 }
9575
9576 char buff[ARBITRARY_BUFF_SIZE];
9577 ParticleSystemTemplate* otherTemp;
9578
9579 ((funcptr) proc)(0, buff, &otherTemp); // PARM_ParticleTypeName
9580 if (otherTemp == particleTemplate) {
9581 particleTemplate->m_particleTypeName.set(buff);
9582 }
9583
9584
9585 ((funcptr) proc)(1, buff, &otherTemp); // PARM_SlaveSystemName
9586 if (otherTemp == particleTemplate) {
9587 particleTemplate->m_slaveSystemName.set(buff);
9588 }
9589
9590 ((funcptr) proc)(2, buff, &otherTemp); // PARM_AttachedSystemName
9591 if (otherTemp == particleTemplate) {
9592 particleTemplate->m_attachedSystemName.set(buff);
9593 }
9594}
9595
9596extern void _updateAsciiStringParmsFromSystem( ParticleSystemTemplate *particleTemplate )
9597{
9598 typedef void (*funcptr)(int, const char*, ParticleSystemTemplate**);
9599
9600 if (!st_ParticleDLL || !particleTemplate) {
9601 return;
9602 }
9603
9604 FARPROC proc;
9605 proc = GetProcAddress(st_ParticleDLL, "UpdateParticleAsciiStringParm");
9606
9607 if (!proc) {
9608 return;
9609 }
9610
9611 ((funcptr) proc)(0, particleTemplate->m_particleTypeName.str(), NULL); // PARM_ParticleTypeName
9612 ((funcptr) proc)(1, particleTemplate->m_slaveSystemName.str(), NULL); // PARM_SlaveSystemName
9613 ((funcptr) proc)(2, particleTemplate->m_attachedSystemName.str(), NULL); // PARM_AttachedSystemName
9614
9615}

9617#define BACKUP_FILE_NAME "Data\\INI\\ParticleSystem"
9618#define BACKUP_EXT "BAK"
9619static void _writeOutINI( void )
9620{
9621 // currently, this uses NO intelligence. It blindly iterates through all of the
9622 // particle system templates and writes out every field that it thinks it should.
9623 const int maxFileLength = 128;
9624 char buff[maxFileLength];
9625
9626 File *saveFile = NULL;
9627
9628 int i = 0;
9629 do {
9630 if (saveFile) {
9631 saveFile->close();
9632 saveFile = NULL;
9633 }
9634 sprintf(buff, "%s%d.%s", BACKUP_FILE_NAME, i, BACKUP_EXT);
9635 saveFile = TheFileSystem->openFile(buff, File::READ | File::TEXT);
9636 ++i;
9637 } while (saveFile);
9638
9639 saveFile = TheFileSystem->openFile(buff, File::WRITE | File::TEXT);
9640 if (!saveFile) {
9641 return;
9642 }
9643
9644 // save the old file
9645 File *oldINI = TheFileSystem->openFile("Data\\INI\\ParticleSystem.ini", File::READ | File::TEXT);
9646
9647 if (oldINI) {
9648 char singleChar;
9649 while (oldINI->position() != oldINI->size()) {
9650 oldINI->read(&singleChar, 1);
9651 saveFile->write(&singleChar, 1);
9652 }
9653 oldINI->close();
9654 oldINI = NULL;
9655 saveFile->close();
9656 saveFile = NULL;
9657
9658 }
9659
9660
9661 // open the .ini file for writing, truncate.
9662 File *newINI = TheFileSystem->openFile("Data\\INI\\ParticleSystem.ini", File::WRITE | File::TEXT);
9663
9664 if (!newINI) {
9665 DEBUG_CRASH(("Unable to open ParticleSystem.ini. Is it write protected?"));
9666 return;
9667 }
9668
9669 ParticleSystemManager::TemplateMap::iterator begin(TheParticleSystemManager->beginParticleSystemTemplate());
9670 ParticleSystemManager::TemplateMap::iterator end(TheParticleSystemManager->endParticleSystemTemplate());
9671
9672 for (; begin != end; ++begin) {
9673 _writeSingleParticleSystem(newINI, (*begin).second);
9674 }
9675
9676 newINI->close();
9677 newINI = NULL;
9678}

9786void _writeSingleParticleSystem( File *out, ParticleSystemTemplate *templ )
9787{
9788 if (!templ || !out || templ->getName().isEmpty()) {
9789 // sanity
9790 return;
9791 }
9792
9793 static char buff1[ARBITRARY_BUFF_SIZE];
9794 static char buff2[ARBITRARY_BUFF_SIZE];
9795 static char buff3[ARBITRARY_BUFF_SIZE];
9796 static char buff4[ARBITRARY_BUFF_SIZE];
9797
9798
9799 // the .append looks REALLY ugly, but this code was written with streams in mind, and so
9800 // these were all originally << (feed-operator for streams)
9801 // I might come back and re-write this later, if there are enough complaints. ;-) jkmcd
9802 // in the meantime, move along...
9803 std::string thisEntry = "";
9804 thisEntry.append(HEADER).append(SEP_SPACE).append(templ->getName().str()).append(SEP_EOL);
9805 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_PRIORITY).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(ParticlePriorityNames[templ->m_priority]).append(SEP_EOL);
9806 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_ISONESHOT).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append((templ->m_isOneShot ? STR_TRUE : STR_FALSE)).append(SEP_EOL);
9807 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_SHADER).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(ParticleShaderTypeNames[templ->m_shaderType]).append(SEP_EOL);
9808 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_TYPE).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(ParticleTypeNames[templ->m_particleType]).append(SEP_EOL);
9809 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_PARTICLENAME).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(templ->m_particleTypeName.str()).append(SEP_EOL);
9810
9811 sprintf(buff1, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_angleZ.getMinimumValue());
9812 sprintf(buff2, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_angleZ.getMaximumValue());
9813 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_ANGLEZ).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(buff1).append(SEP_SPACE).append(buff2).append(SEP_EOL);
9814
9815 sprintf(buff1, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_angularRateZ.getMinimumValue());
9816 sprintf(buff2, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_angularRateZ.getMaximumValue());
9817 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_ANGLERATEZ).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(buff1).append(SEP_SPACE).append(buff2).append(SEP_EOL);
9818
9819 sprintf(buff1, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_angularDamping.getMinimumValue());
9820 sprintf(buff2, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_angularDamping.getMaximumValue());
9821 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_ANGLEDAMP).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(buff1).append(SEP_SPACE).append(buff2).append(SEP_EOL);
9822
9823 sprintf(buff1, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_velDamping.getMinimumValue());
9824 sprintf(buff2, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_velDamping.getMaximumValue());
9825 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_VELOCITYDAMP).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(buff1).append(SEP_SPACE).append(buff2).append(SEP_EOL);
9826
9827 sprintf(buff1, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_gravity);
9828 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_GRAVITY).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(buff1).append(SEP_EOL);
9829 if (!templ->m_slaveSystemName.isEmpty()) {
9830 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_SLAVESYSTEM).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(templ->m_slaveSystemName.str()).append(SEP_EOL);
9831 sprintf(buff1, FORMAT_STRING_LEADING_STRING, STR_X.c_str(), templ->m_slavePosOffset.x);
9832 sprintf(buff2, FORMAT_STRING_LEADING_STRING, STR_Y.c_str(), templ->m_slavePosOffset.y);
9833 sprintf(buff3, FORMAT_STRING_LEADING_STRING, STR_Z.c_str(), templ->m_slavePosOffset.z);
9834 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_SLAVEPOS).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(buff1).append(SEP_SPACE).append(buff2).append(SEP_SPACE).append(buff3).append(SEP_EOL);
9835 }
9836
9837 if (!templ->m_attachedSystemName.isEmpty()) {
9838 thisEntry.append(SEP_HEAD).append(F_ATTACHED).append(EQ_WITH_SPACES).append(templ->m_attachedSystemName.str()).append(SEP_EOL);
9839 }
9840
9841 sprintf(buff1, FORMAT_STRING, templ->m_lifetime.getMinimumValue());

10078
10079static int _getEditorBehavior( void )
10080{
10081 typedef int (*funcptr)( void );
10082
10083 if (!st_ParticleDLL) {
10084 return 0x00;
10085 }
10086
10087 FARPROC proc;
10088 proc = GetProcAddress(st_ParticleDLL, "NextParticleEditorBehavior");
10089
10090 if (!proc) {
10091 return 0x00;
10092 }
10093
10094 return ((funcptr)proc)();
10095}
10096
10097static void _updateAndSetCurrentSystem( void )
10098{
10099 AsciiString particleSystemName = _getParticleSystemName();
10100 _addUpdatedParticleSystem(particleSystemName);
10101 ParticleSystemTemplate *pTemp = const_cast<ParticleSystemTemplate*>(TheParticleSystemManager->findTemplate(particleSystemName));
10102 if (pTemp) {
10103 _updateAsciiStringParmsToSystem(pTemp);
10104 _updateAsciiStringParmsFromSystem(pTemp);
10105 _updatePanelParameters(pTemp);
10106
10107 if( st_particleSystemNeedsStopping )
10108 {
10109 st_particleSystem->stop();
10110 st_particleSystem->destroy();
10111 st_particleSystemNeedsStopping = FALSE;
10112 }
10113 st_particleSystem = TheParticleSystemManager->createParticleSystem(pTemp);
10114 if( st_particleSystem )
10115 {
10116 if( st_particleSystem->isSystemForever() )
10117 st_particleSystemNeedsStopping = TRUE;// Only infinite lifetime systems need to be stopped.
10118 // You can't stop others, because you can't know if they have deleted themselves. That used
10119 // to be a tiny memory overwrite, now it is a crash since destroy() now has a function call.
10120
10121 ParticleSystemTemplate *parentTemp = TheParticleSystemManager->findParentTemplate(pTemp->getName(), 0);
10122 if (parentTemp) {
10123 ParticleSystem *parentSystem = NULL;
10124 parentSystem = TheParticleSystemManager->createParticleSystem(parentTemp);
10125
10126 if (parentSystem) {
10127 ParticleSystem::mergeRelatedParticleSystems(parentSystem, st_particleSystem, true);
10128 parentSystem->stop();
10129 parentSystem->destroy();
10130 }
10131 }
10132
10133 Coord3D pos;
10134 pos.x = pos.y = 50 * MAP_XY_FACTOR;
10135 pos.z = TheTerrainLogic->getGroundHeight(pos.x, pos.y) + 5 * MAP_XY_FACTOR;
10136 st_particleSystem->setPosition(&pos);
10137 }
10138 }
10139}
10140
10141static void _reloadParticleSystemFromINI( AsciiString particleSystemName )
10142{
10143 if (!st_ParticleDLL || particleSystemName.isEmpty()) {
10144 return;
10145 }
10146
10147 // Here's what we're doing
10148 // Find the entry in Data\\INI\\ParticleSystem.ini
10149 // put that whole entry into a temp file
10150 // force the INI to reload with INI_LOAD_OVERWRITE
10151 // force the particle system editor to recognize that the system has changed without its consent.
10152
10153 static char linebuff[INI_MAX_CHARS_PER_LINE + 1];
10154 linebuff[0] = 0;
10155
10156 // save the old file
10157 File *iniFile = TheFileSystem->openFile("Data\\INI\\ParticleSystem.ini", File::READ | File::TEXT);
10158 File *outTempINI = NULL;
10159
10160 if (!iniFile) {
10161 return;
10162 }
10163
10164 try {
10165 // find the entry
10166 while (!((iniFile->eof()) || INI::isDeclarationOfType("ParticleSystem", particleSystemName, linebuff))) {
10167 iniFile->nextLine(linebuff, INI_MAX_CHARS_PER_LINE);
10168 }
10169
10170 { // copy it to a temp file
10171 if (iniFile->eof()) {
10172 throw 0;
10173 }
10174
10175 outTempINI = TheFileSystem->openFile("temporary.ini", File::WRITE | File::TEXT);
10176 if (!outTempINI) {
10177 throw 0;
10178 }
10179
10180
10181 while (!(iniFile->eof() || INI::isEndOfBlock(linebuff)) ) {
10182 outTempINI->write(linebuff, strlen(linebuff));
10183 iniFile->nextLine(linebuff, INI_MAX_CHARS_PER_LINE);
10184 }
10185
10186 if (iniFile->eof()) {
10187 throw 1;
10188 }
10189
10190
10191 // write out the closing "END"
10192 outTempINI->write(linebuff, strlen(linebuff));
10193 outTempINI->close();
10194 outTempINI = NULL;
10195 }
10196
10197 // force the current system to stop.
10198 if (st_particleSystemNeedsStopping)
10199 {
10200 st_particleSystem->stop();
10201 st_particleSystem->destroy();
10202 st_particleSystemNeedsStopping = FALSE;
10203 }
10204 // reload that entry
10205 INI ini;
10206 ini.load("temporary.ini", INI_LOAD_OVERWRITE, NULL);
10207
10208 // delete the file
10209// unlink("temporary.ini");
10210
10211 // force the particle system to update itself
10212 ParticleSystemTemplate *pTemp = const_cast<ParticleSystemTemplate*>(TheParticleSystemManager->findTemplate(particleSystemName));
10213 _updateAsciiStringParmsFromSystem(pTemp);
10214 _updatePanelParameters(pTemp);
10215
10216 } catch (int why) {
10217 switch(why)
10218 {
10219 case 2:
10220 case 1: if (outTempINI) { outTempINI->close(); }
10221 case 0: if (iniFile) { iniFile->close(); }
10222 }
10223 }
10224
10225}

10227static int _getNewCurrentParticleCap( void )
10228{
10229 typedef int (*funcptr)( void );
10230
10231 if (!st_ParticleDLL) {
10232 return -1;
10233 }
10234
10235 FARPROC proc;
10236 proc = GetProcAddress(st_ParticleDLL, "GetNewParticleCap");
10237
10238 if (!proc) {
10239 return -1;
10240 }
10241
10242 return ((funcptr)proc)();
10243}

10288static void _initVTune()
10289{
10290 // always try loading it, even if -vtune wasn't specified.
10291 st_vTuneDLL = ::LoadLibrary("vtuneapi.dll");
10292// nope, not here...
10293//DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(st_vTuneDLL != NULL, "VTuneAPI DLL not found!"));
10294
10295 if (st_vTuneDLL)
10296 {
10297 VTPause = (VTProc)::GetProcAddress(st_vTuneDLL, "VTPause");
10298 VTResume = (VTProc)::GetProcAddress(st_vTuneDLL, "VTResume");
10299 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(VTPause != NULL && VTResume != NULL, ("VTuneAPI procs not found!\n"));
10300 }
10301 else
10302 {
10303 VTPause = NULL;
10304 VTResume = NULL;
10305 }
10306
10307 if (TheGlobalData->m_vTune)
10308 {
10309 // if -vtune was specified, start it paused.
10310 st_EnableVTune = false;
10311 if (VTPause)
10312 VTPause();
10313 // only complain about it being missing if they were expecting it to be present
10314 DEBUG_ASSERTCRASH(st_vTuneDLL != NULL, ("VTuneAPI DLL not found!\n"));
10315 }
10316 else
10317 {
10318 // otherwise enable it.
10319 st_EnableVTune = true;
10320 if (VTResume)
10321 VTResume();
10322 }
10323}
10324
10325static void _updateVTune()
10326{
10327 if (!st_vTuneDLL)
10328 return;
10329
10330 if (st_EnableVTune)
10331 {
10332 if (VTResume)
10333 VTResume();
10334 }
10335 else
10336 {
10337 if (VTPause)
10338 VTPause();
10339 }
10340}
10341
10342static void _cleanUpVTune()
10343{
10344 if (st_vTuneDLL)
10345 {
10346 FreeLibrary(st_vTuneDLL);
10347 }
10348 st_vTuneDLL = NULL;
10349 VTPause = NULL;
10350 VTResume = NULL;
10351}
